WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:49.074 --> 01:51.201
Always remember
your promise to me.

01:51.276 --> 01:54.439
Never let nobody or nothing
turn you into no cripple.

02:16.335 --> 02:17.461
All right!

02:17.536 --> 02:19.094
Rest stop, 45 minutes.

02:19.238 --> 02:21.468
Come on, folks.
We gotta move.

02:21.740 --> 02:24.800
We leave at 2:45 p. M.
On the dot. Can't be late.

02:25.811 --> 02:28.041
Hot meals
and bathrooms inside.

02:28.881 --> 02:30.872
All right, uh, there's a
window out back

02:30.949 --> 02:32.314
for y'all to buy sandwiches.

02:32.384 --> 02:34.909
And I suggest you make
good use of them outhouses.

02:34.987 --> 02:37.387
Ain't nothing but bushes
for you in the Carolinas.

02:37.456 --> 02:38.718
Sir.

02:41.226 --> 02:42.693
Can I help you, sir?

02:42.761 --> 02:43.853
Yes, sir.

02:45.164 --> 02:46.392
Seattle?

02:47.766 --> 02:49.028
Who you riding with?

02:49.101 --> 02:50.693
Nobody. Just me.

02:50.836 --> 02:53.361
Boy, I can't take
responsibility

02:53.438 --> 02:56.305
for some blind nigger
traveling 3,500 miles alone.

02:56.375 --> 02:58.570
I... I... I paid for this here
ticket, and it says

02:58.644 --> 03:00.669
that you have to take me
to Seattle.

03:00.846 --> 03:03.371
Don't you be smarting off
to me, boy.

03:04.249 --> 03:06.513
With all due respect, sir,
I earned the right.

03:06.585 --> 03:08.485
I may have left my eyes
on Omaha Beach,

03:08.554 --> 03:10.647
but I ain't asking no charity
from Uncle Sam.

03:10.722 --> 03:12.986
I got a job waiting
for me in Seattle.

03:14.426 --> 03:15.654
You were in Normandy?

03:15.727 --> 03:18.025
Shuttling troopers
to the beach.

03:18.497 --> 03:20.294
We took a direct hit.

03:25.404 --> 03:26.769
I'm sorry, son.

03:28.540 --> 03:30.599
I'll keep an eye on you
myself.

03:30.676 --> 03:33.008
Come on.
Take a seat in the back.

03:40.419 --> 03:43.217
<i># Any time #</i>

03:43.455 --> 03:47.255
<i># You're feeling lonely #</i>

03:47.392 --> 03:50.293
<i># Anytime #</i>

03:50.362 --> 03:52.626
<i># You're feeling blue #</i>

03:54.199 --> 03:56.929
<i># Anytime #</i>

03:57.135 --> 04:00.161
<i># Anytime you feel
down hearted #</i>

04:01.073 --> 04:05.772
<i># That will prove
your love for me is true #</i>

04:07.779 --> 04:10.407
<i># Anytime #</i>

04:10.649 --> 04:13.812
<i># You're thinkin' about me ##</i>

04:17.089 --> 04:19.353
Til, what the hell
do you think you're doin'?

04:19.423 --> 04:21.415
Billy, don't get
your feathers all ruffled now.

04:21.493 --> 04:24.223
I met this ol' boy over
at the O.C. At Clarkfield,

04:24.296 --> 04:25.888
and well, he plays
a mean jazz piano.

04:25.964 --> 04:28.262
<i>I don't care if he whistles
Dixie out his ass.</i>

04:28.333 --> 04:30.301
He ain't gonna
do it here.

04:30.369 --> 04:31.700
Sir.

04:31.937 --> 04:33.700
Boy, are you blind?

04:33.772 --> 04:35.399
Yes, sir.
Since I was seven.

04:37.175 --> 04:38.870
Well, let me help you
out then.

04:38.944 --> 04:41.071
This is a country band.

04:41.213 --> 04:43.443
We don't play
no boogie-woogie.

04:43.715 --> 04:46.081
Uh, yes, I understand.
I love country music.

04:46.151 --> 04:48.676
All right, go on.
Tell me.

04:48.754 --> 04:51.222
What is it you love
about country music?

04:51.290 --> 04:52.587
I... I love the stories.

04:52.658 --> 04:54.216
Uh, you know,
about fallin' in love

04:54.293 --> 04:55.954
and having love
knock you around

04:56.028 --> 04:58.019
and then the pressures
of the world on you so tough.

04:58.096 --> 04:59.324
It... It makes you
feel small.

04:59.398 --> 05:00.831
You want to give
your soul to God.

05:00.899 --> 05:02.867
You might as well.
Your ass belongs to Him.

05:11.977 --> 05:13.444
Boy, are you sure
you blind?

05:13.512 --> 05:14.911
Last time I checked.

05:27.993 --> 05:29.460
Okay. Come on in.

05:43.608 --> 05:46.042
Billy,
I think you're outvoted.

05:46.378 --> 05:48.505
Til, one hint of trouble,

05:48.580 --> 05:50.377
and your blind nigra's
out of here.

05:52.250 --> 05:53.342
Damn!

05:53.985 --> 05:55.077
Here.

05:55.220 --> 05:57.711
I'm gonna have
to put some glasses

05:57.789 --> 06:00.417
before he scares
somebody half to death.

06:10.202 --> 06:11.965
Seattle, Washington, folks.

06:12.037 --> 06:14.028
Change bus here
for all points north:

06:14.106 --> 06:15.733
Bellingham, Mount Vernon.

06:15.807 --> 06:17.468
Vancouver, Canada.

06:36.094 --> 06:38.358
<i>Uh, that's Diz. Emanon.</i>

06:39.297 --> 06:41.197
Yeah. But what's it
spell backwards?

06:41.266 --> 06:42.528
Ah... ah... ah, come on, man.

06:42.601 --> 06:44.831
Why don't you give me
something difficult?

06:44.903 --> 06:46.165
"No Name."

06:47.639 --> 06:49.732
Say, daddy-o,
what ax you play?

06:49.808 --> 06:50.775
Uh, piano.

06:50.842 --> 06:52.207
Just blew in
from Tampa, Florida.

06:52.277 --> 06:54.142
Me and my partner,
Gossie McGee, came here,

06:54.212 --> 06:55.839
you know, want to
fatten up our style.

06:55.914 --> 06:58.212
Cop some licks from some more
experienced cats. You dig?

06:58.283 --> 06:59.477
You know what?

06:59.551 --> 07:01.143
Why don't you let me
take you inside?

07:01.219 --> 07:02.345
You know,
show you around.

07:02.421 --> 07:03.979
All right.
Perfect gentleman.
Yeah.

07:04.055 --> 07:05.522
This is just
like my place.

07:05.590 --> 07:06.784
So, what's your name?

07:06.858 --> 07:07.916
Ray Robinson.

07:07.993 --> 07:09.051
I'm Quincy Jones.

07:09.127 --> 07:10.116
Quincy Jones.

07:10.195 --> 07:12.493
Hey, Gerry!
This here's my man, Ray.

07:12.564 --> 07:14.327
He's here to see his friend,
Gossie McGee.

07:14.399 --> 07:15.889
So I figured
I'll show him inside...

07:15.967 --> 07:18.162
Don't mess with me, Q.
He can come in, but not you.

07:18.236 --> 07:20.670
Vice is on my ass for letting
you underage kids in.

07:20.739 --> 07:21.899
Get out of here, Q.

07:21.973 --> 07:23.440
Can't you see...
Get out of here, Q.

07:23.508 --> 07:25.305
He's blind!
I gotta show him in.
Get out.

07:25.377 --> 07:27.174
Jive-ass.
What?

07:27.245 --> 07:29.975
Hey, Ray Robinson,
when am I gonna
hear you play, baby?

07:30.048 --> 07:31.675
Uh, well,
that may cost you.

07:32.417 --> 07:37.218
Welcome, all you cool cats
and fine felines.

07:37.289 --> 07:40.224
You've come to the place
where the sophisti-cats
and hipsters

07:40.292 --> 07:42.157
hang their bebop hats.

07:42.327 --> 07:44.522
So snuggle up
and come near

07:44.596 --> 07:48.157
for tonight is Talent Night
at The Rocking Chair.

07:48.600 --> 07:51.626
Let's hear it
for Dancin' Al!

08:01.246 --> 08:04.579
Gossie's been cattin' around
with one of my waitresses
since he got here.

08:04.649 --> 08:07.777
He never told me
that his partner
was a blind 'Bama boy.

08:07.986 --> 08:10.284
Marlene,
Demurs just called.

08:10.355 --> 08:12.255
Thurmond's sick.

08:12.491 --> 08:13.753
What about Sassy?

08:13.825 --> 08:15.019
Flat tire.

08:22.534 --> 08:26.061
Okay, 'Bama.
Why don't you get on up there
and show me what you got?

08:26.204 --> 08:29.139
Well, I-I'm not
prepared to do my thing
right now, tonight...

08:29.207 --> 08:31.368
This is the only audition
you're going to get, puddin'.

08:31.443 --> 08:35.004
So either get on up there,
or you and Gossie can haul
your asses back down South.

08:35.080 --> 08:37.014
Here. Smoke some of this.

08:40.919 --> 08:42.580
This ain't no tobacco, man.

08:42.654 --> 08:44.519
No, hold it in,
it'll calm you down.

08:44.589 --> 08:45.954
All right, Oberon.

08:46.024 --> 08:47.491
Get on up there
and introduce him.

08:47.559 --> 08:48.958
Yes, ma'am.

08:49.394 --> 08:51.794
Okay, 'Bama. Let's go.

08:53.131 --> 08:54.325
Yeah.

08:56.902 --> 09:01.202
Now, I got something special
for all you satin dolls.

09:01.306 --> 09:04.002
And I don't mean
Oberon's big thunder.

09:05.210 --> 09:06.905
Now that's
for another show.

09:06.978 --> 09:09.208
Now we got some
new blood for ya.

09:09.281 --> 09:11.408
Yeah, straight off
the bus from Florida,

09:11.483 --> 09:16.318
I give you Ray
"Don't Call Me Sugar"
Robinson!

09:25.730 --> 09:27.027
How y'all doing tonight?

09:27.098 --> 09:28.326
Better than you!

09:31.336 --> 09:32.564
Relax, Ray. Relax.

09:32.637 --> 09:33.797
I got it.

09:38.276 --> 09:39.641
Uh-uh, what do y'all
want to hear?

09:43.648 --> 09:45.548
<i>How about
a little Nat King Cole?</i>

09:52.057 --> 09:53.957
Y'all like Nat King Cole?

09:56.995 --> 10:01.261
# If you ever plan
to travel west #

10:02.934 --> 10:04.196
'Bama ain't bad.

10:04.269 --> 10:06.032
Yeah, I'd say
he saved our asses.

10:08.506 --> 10:10.337
What the hell is
Ray doin' up there?

10:10.475 --> 10:12.306
Auditioning for you,
Gossie.

10:12.911 --> 10:14.845
He ain't no good without me.

10:15.880 --> 10:18.815
How'd you and the 'Bama
like to do a week
here at the Chair?

10:18.883 --> 10:20.282
I know a good bass player.

10:20.352 --> 10:23.651
A nice jazz trio could score
big with the right manager.

10:24.522 --> 10:25.716
Manager?

10:26.391 --> 10:28.450
Come on now, Gossie,
don't be so small-minded.

10:28.526 --> 10:30.084
You know
you've got to give to get.

10:30.161 --> 10:32.152
Now what exactly do I
have to give?

10:32.230 --> 10:33.595
25 percent.

10:33.665 --> 10:35.189
But I'll be gettin' you
other gigs.

10:35.266 --> 10:38.167
All right,
next question: What do I get?

10:38.870 --> 10:40.201
What do you need?

10:40.271 --> 10:43.172
Double scale as leader,
plus 10 percent.

10:44.542 --> 10:45.839
What about the 'Bama?

10:45.910 --> 10:48.401
He's about as green
as a blade of grass.

10:49.247 --> 10:50.509
I can handle him.

10:50.582 --> 10:52.209
# Flagstaff, Arizona #

10:52.751 --> 10:53.911
Yeah, he's green.

10:53.985 --> 10:55.452
# Kingman, Barstow #

10:55.520 --> 10:57.283
So, Gossie,
you don't need to worry

10:57.355 --> 10:58.879
about a hotel room
for the 'Bama.

10:59.190 --> 11:00.953
He can flop at my place.

11:01.993 --> 11:03.620
Hey, y'all never change.

11:03.695 --> 11:07.688
# Get your kicks
on Route sixty-six ##

11:10.935 --> 11:13.199
Ray, you coming back to bed?

11:14.739 --> 11:16.138
I'm getting some water.

11:16.207 --> 11:19.108
I can see that,
but mama ain't finished yet.

11:19.744 --> 11:21.541
<i>For the first time anywhere,</i>

11:21.613 --> 11:24.582
<i>let's hear it
for The McSon Trio!</i>

11:24.649 --> 11:27.277
# A buzzard took the monkey
for a ride in the air #

11:27.352 --> 11:30.446
# The monkey thought that
everything was on the square #

11:30.522 --> 11:31.989
Ray, when you
coming out?

11:32.057 --> 11:33.319
In a minute.

11:33.858 --> 11:37.259
Mama's got some more
blackberry cobbler
for you, baby.

11:37.896 --> 11:39.022
Damn.

11:40.765 --> 11:43.131
# Straighten up
and fly right #

11:43.201 --> 11:45.726
# Cool down, papa,
don't you blow your top ##

11:54.813 --> 11:56.872
Marlene, if you're gonna
send us out on tour,

11:56.948 --> 11:58.540
we're gonna need
more than $5 a day.

11:58.616 --> 12:00.675
How come we can't get paid
after each gig?

12:00.752 --> 12:02.913
Because you boys will spend
everything you make.

12:02.987 --> 12:05.888
The club sends the checks
to me, so as I can bank them.

12:05.957 --> 12:08.357
I just want to see
my own checks, that's all.

12:08.426 --> 12:11.293
You don't see, Ray.
You're blind, baby.

12:11.362 --> 12:13.057
Or did you forget?

12:13.698 --> 12:17.156
Now, you want to go out
on your own
and see how well you do?

12:25.210 --> 12:27.940
Ray! Hey, Marlene,
where's Ray?

12:28.012 --> 12:30.947
He's in the back bedroom.
And wipe your feet.

12:36.621 --> 12:40.614
Ray, uh, six-nine,
where you at?
Six-nine. Six-nine.

12:41.893 --> 12:44.293
Lionel Hampton just asked me
to go on the road
with him, man!

12:44.362 --> 12:45.920
Lionel Hampton, man!

12:45.997 --> 12:47.828
Sure he did.
Then why you still here?

12:47.899 --> 12:51.858
And dig this:
His wife, she kicked me off
the tour bus.

12:51.936 --> 12:54.769
Told me to come back
when I started shaving.
You believe that?

12:54.839 --> 12:57.967
Uh... uh, Seven-oh, could you
do me a favor, man,
and close that bag for me?

12:58.042 --> 13:00.374
What's wrong?
You got two hands.
You can close it yourself.

13:00.445 --> 13:02.208
I got two feet, too.
Could you close it?

13:02.280 --> 13:03.872
I got it.

13:05.850 --> 13:07.477
Excuse me, sir!

13:08.920 --> 13:11.081
Man, we're gonna be late.

13:11.523 --> 13:13.855
I got to get
my own place, Gossie.

13:14.492 --> 13:17.825
Why? I mean,
you got free rent right now.

13:18.029 --> 13:19.997
Like hell it's free rent.

13:24.135 --> 13:25.363
Oh, come on, Ray.

13:25.436 --> 13:27.336
Why you gonna mess
with a good thing?

13:27.405 --> 13:29.703
All I'm saying is you keep
layin' that pipe with Marlene,

13:29.774 --> 13:31.708
and I bet you she's gonna
make us all rich.

13:31.776 --> 13:33.607
Hey, sir, excuse me!

13:40.185 --> 13:41.709
# Straighten up
and fly right #

13:42.620 --> 13:44.850
# Straighten up
and stay right #

13:45.156 --> 13:47.488
# Straighten up
and fly right #

13:47.559 --> 13:48.753
# Cool down, papa #

13:48.827 --> 13:53.696
# Don't you blow your top ##

14:00.738 --> 14:02.763
<i>Just back from their
triumphant tour</i>

14:02.841 --> 14:06.242
<i>of the Yakima Valley,
The McSon Trio!</i>

14:06.411 --> 14:07.901
<i>They'll be back right here,</i>

14:07.979 --> 14:10.243
<i>same time, same place,
next week.</i>

14:14.285 --> 14:18.051
Hey, baby, you sound
more like Nat
than the King himself.

14:19.924 --> 14:21.016
What's your name?

14:21.092 --> 14:22.116
Ray Robinson.

14:22.327 --> 14:23.487
Ray Robinson?

14:23.561 --> 14:26.086
I'm Jack Lauderdale,
Swing Time Records.

14:26.164 --> 14:29.099
Oh, hey... hey, hey, Jack!
How you doing, man?

14:29.167 --> 14:30.361
Good.
Oh, good.

14:30.435 --> 14:32.062
How about us makin'
a record together?

14:32.136 --> 14:34.195
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Hell, yeah! Let's do that.

14:34.272 --> 14:35.466
Can I help you?

14:35.540 --> 14:36.564
I don't think so.

14:36.641 --> 14:38.939
We're just talking
a little business.

14:39.010 --> 14:42.173
Then you need to talk to me,
'cause I'm his manager.

14:42.580 --> 14:43.979
Whichever way
the wind blows.

14:44.048 --> 14:45.174
It's blowing.

14:45.250 --> 14:46.808
Jack Lauderdale,
Swing Time Records.

14:46.885 --> 14:48.750
Marlene Andres.
Marlene?

14:48.820 --> 14:50.310
Gossie McGee.
Gossie McGee.

14:50.388 --> 14:51.582
Great set, baby.

14:51.656 --> 14:53.624
We're going to talk
with Mr. Lauderdale here.

14:53.691 --> 14:55.022
Come on, Jack.
I'm buying.

14:55.093 --> 14:56.526
I'm coming in, uh,
to talk to him.

14:56.594 --> 14:58.653
You are doing
a fabulous job!

14:58.730 --> 14:59.754
Yes, man.

14:59.831 --> 15:01.822
Eh, look, let's talk to him
about this record.

15:01.900 --> 15:03.993
Hey, no, no, we're gonna
let Marlene handle that.

15:04.068 --> 15:06.002
You get Oberon
to call you a cab, all right.

15:06.070 --> 15:07.628
Great set, Ray.

15:08.740 --> 15:09.934
Goss!

15:10.008 --> 15:12.101
Hey, daddy-o, want a smoke?

15:12.677 --> 15:14.645
I got some gage,
fresh off the boat.

15:14.712 --> 15:16.179
It's clean and seedless.

15:16.247 --> 15:18.010
So that's how it is, huh?

15:18.216 --> 15:21.014
You keep me high
while they talk the business?

15:21.486 --> 15:23.818
I ain't the one
playing you, man.

15:24.422 --> 15:25.821
Oberon, listen...

15:27.592 --> 15:30.959
You know, Marlene and Gossie
are the ones running
the game on you, Ray.

15:31.029 --> 15:32.087
What?

15:32.163 --> 15:34.688
They sliced up the pie
the first night you played.

15:34.766 --> 15:36.495
35 percent off the top.

15:36.567 --> 15:38.592
Plus Gossie's
double scale as leader.

15:39.037 --> 15:40.299
Leader?
If anybody's leading the band,

15:40.371 --> 15:42.566
I'm the one
that's the leader.

15:42.874 --> 15:44.398
Forget the bo' humps.
You know what?

15:44.475 --> 15:45.840
I... I'm... I'm gonna go
my own way.

15:45.910 --> 15:47.775
Who's gonna
book your gigs?

15:47.912 --> 15:49.812
Marlene's got you locked up.

15:49.881 --> 15:52.679
And she ain't gonna give up
her golden goose.

15:52.784 --> 15:55.480
# Straighten up
and fly right #

15:55.553 --> 15:58.078
# Cool down, papa,
don't you blow your top ##

15:58.156 --> 16:00.351
Hey, Ray Robinson,
you are fantastic.

16:01.259 --> 16:03.557
There you go.
Give me some skin.

16:05.163 --> 16:06.255
What's that?

16:06.331 --> 16:07.491
Jack's card.

16:07.598 --> 16:09.691
I got his number
at the hotel.

16:15.506 --> 16:17.474
Come on, Q.
It's not that complicated.

16:17.542 --> 16:18.873
Now let's just play it again.

16:18.943 --> 16:20.774
That's a B flat,
C 7, scale it up,

16:20.845 --> 16:22.779
and triple it off
the back end.

16:25.083 --> 16:27.244
Yeah, nigger!
Yeah, that's it.

16:28.786 --> 16:31.846
Ray, what did I tell you
about cookin' in the dark?

16:31.923 --> 16:33.584
Are you tryin'
to burn the house down?

16:33.658 --> 16:36.183
Think about it, Marlene.
Uh... uh, What do I need
the light for?

16:36.260 --> 16:38.023
Well, you don't need
to be cookin' anyway.

16:38.096 --> 16:39.654
We brought you
takeout from Oscar's.

16:39.731 --> 16:40.789
Well, get your money back.

16:40.865 --> 16:42.230
I got fried chicken
right here.

16:42.300 --> 16:43.597
Come on, Seven-oh,
try this.

16:43.668 --> 16:45.158
Yeah! About time.

16:47.005 --> 16:48.836
Hey, that's home-cooked,
right there.

16:48.906 --> 16:50.066
Mmm, no, thank you.

16:50.141 --> 16:51.540
This chicken
is the mostest, huh.

16:51.609 --> 16:53.873
Just needs a little hot sauce
and it'll be perfect.

16:53.945 --> 16:55.970
Yeah. So, what did
Jack Lauderdale have to say?

16:56.047 --> 16:57.639
Oh, I clocked him
comin' out the gate.

16:57.715 --> 16:58.977
He's a two-bit hustler.

16:59.050 --> 17:00.210
Oh, I see.

17:00.284 --> 17:02.809
Yeah, turns out the only hit
that Swing Time ever had

17:02.887 --> 17:05.082
<i>was Open the Door, Richard,
which was a joke record.</i>

17:05.156 --> 17:07.021
Uh... uh... uh, what about him
recordin' me?

17:07.090 --> 17:09.457
Oh, he'll record you,
if we pay the freight.

17:09.627 --> 17:11.253
Scratch a liar,
find a thief.

17:12.363 --> 17:13.887
What's that
supposed to mean?

17:13.964 --> 17:15.159
This.

17:15.900 --> 17:17.800
You see I saw
Jack Lauderdale tonight,

17:17.868 --> 17:19.894
and he gave me a $500
advance on my record.

17:19.971 --> 17:22.234
He also said he'll put me
on the road with Lowell Fulson

17:22.306 --> 17:23.829
and pay me three times
what you pay.

17:23.907 --> 17:25.034
Now, that's a lie!

17:25.108 --> 17:28.545
Hey, no way he's not gonna
put some blind man
on the road. Think about it.

17:28.613 --> 17:30.547
I mean, you... you need
watchin' out for.

17:30.615 --> 17:32.845
And he ain't got the time
to look after you
the way I do.

17:32.917 --> 17:35.351
Is that what
you've been doing, Gossie?
Watchin' out for me?

17:35.420 --> 17:37.285
Is that why you get
paid double what I do?

17:38.823 --> 17:39.983
Who told you that?

17:40.058 --> 17:41.116
It's true, ain't it?

17:41.192 --> 17:43.183
You two have been
gaming me since I got here.

17:43.261 --> 17:45.229
Ray, baby, listen...
I ain't listening to you!

17:45.296 --> 17:47.696
Ray, I've... I've been
meaning to talk to you
about that.

17:47.765 --> 17:49.824
Then why aren't you talkin'?

17:52.203 --> 17:54.433
Um, look, Ray, Ray,
let's not do nothin' stupid.

17:54.505 --> 17:56.268
I might be blind,
but I ain't stupid!

17:56.340 --> 17:58.035
Q., get my bag
from upstairs.

17:58.109 --> 17:59.235
What?
Get it!

17:59.310 --> 18:00.800
Wha... right now?
Now.

18:00.878 --> 18:03.108
Ray, man, we done been
through a whole lot.

18:03.181 --> 18:05.911
Ray, now wait a minute.
I can explain everything.

18:06.217 --> 18:07.912
Think about what you're doing.

18:07.985 --> 18:09.850
Ray, Ray, now you're makin'
a big mistake.

18:09.921 --> 18:11.912
That clown is spoutin'
promises that he can't keep.

18:11.989 --> 18:13.752
You'd be a fool
to follow him.

18:13.825 --> 18:15.156
Ray, Ray,
we'll make a new deal!

18:15.226 --> 18:16.352
Whatever makes you happy!

18:16.427 --> 18:18.361
The deal is
you can lay the pipe now.

18:18.429 --> 18:21.865
You'll break your neck
going down these stairs
by yourself. Hang on.

18:22.300 --> 18:23.358
Oh, man.

18:23.434 --> 18:27.200
Ray, I ain't never seen you
do nothing like that, man.
Never.

18:27.271 --> 18:28.966
That ain't nothing,
Seven-oh.

18:41.953 --> 18:43.784
Stop cheating, Ray.

18:44.622 --> 18:47.250
George, you can't catch me.
Come on.

18:47.325 --> 18:48.656
Aretha!

18:49.393 --> 18:50.690
Come on, George.

18:50.761 --> 18:53.252
Aretha Robinson,
have you lost your mind?

18:53.331 --> 18:56.630
Eula, you promised to split
every wash basket with me,
fair and square!

18:56.701 --> 18:57.793
And I did!

18:57.869 --> 18:58.961
Hell, you did!

18:59.036 --> 19:01.129
You charge white folks
one thing and pay me another.

19:01.205 --> 19:02.638
Now who's gonna
wash these?

19:02.707 --> 19:04.197
You can.
Now pay me my money!

19:07.778 --> 19:09.769
Okay, I'm a-giving you
your two little dollars.

19:09.847 --> 19:11.974
But don't you be expectin'
no more work out of me!

19:12.049 --> 19:13.482
I got all I need
out of you.

19:13.618 --> 19:15.051
Ray and George, come on!

19:15.119 --> 19:16.746
That's right.
Get out of my yard

19:16.821 --> 19:18.584
and don't y'all
never come back!

19:21.492 --> 19:24.256
Y'all got to learn
to read and write real good,

19:24.328 --> 19:27.092
so you never have to work
for people like that.

19:27.165 --> 19:28.860
Scratch a liar,
find a thief.

19:28.933 --> 19:29.900
Understand?

19:29.967 --> 19:31.127
Yes, Mama.

19:44.081 --> 19:46.743
Smell that, Ray.
Smell the success.

19:47.018 --> 19:48.417
We're in LA, man,

19:48.486 --> 19:50.784
the place where the Negro
comes to spread his wings.

19:50.855 --> 19:53.255
You... you know, man, I know
my ears ain't deceivin' me.

19:53.324 --> 19:54.348
Is that Art Tatum?

19:54.425 --> 19:56.086
It sure is, baby.
You want to meet him?

19:56.160 --> 19:58.822
I... I can't meet him.
A- Art Tatum is the most.

20:04.068 --> 20:08.528
So, Ray, we got to talk
about your name, man:
Robinson.

20:08.606 --> 20:11.507
Sugar Ray got the Robinson
franchise all sewed up.

20:11.576 --> 20:15.239
So I'm thinkin' we go with
your middle name, Charles.

20:15.780 --> 20:17.179
As in, Ray Charles.

20:17.248 --> 20:18.977
I don't care
what you call me, man,

20:19.050 --> 20:20.847
just as long as my name's
on the record.

20:20.918 --> 20:22.317
But we're gonna
toast to that.

20:22.386 --> 20:23.683
Hey, what's the haps, Jack?

20:23.754 --> 20:25.381
Oh, my goodness.
Give me some skin.

20:25.456 --> 20:27.515
What's up, baby?
How you doin'?

20:27.592 --> 20:31.187
Lowell Fulson, meet your new
piano player: Ray Charles.

20:31.262 --> 20:33.822
Ray Charles,
the blind sensation.

20:33.898 --> 20:37.698
Ow! Damn! I'm gonna use that
on the album cover.

20:37.768 --> 20:39.201
He's really
the sensation.

20:39.270 --> 20:41.101
I... I love your music,
Mr. Fulson.

20:41.172 --> 20:42.571
Uh, the man's got taste.

20:42.640 --> 20:44.938
Hey, and the man ain't
been on the road

20:45.009 --> 20:47.239
with a band before,
so now you take care of him.

20:47.311 --> 20:48.676
Like my own brother.

20:52.250 --> 20:53.512
Ray.

20:54.385 --> 20:55.511
I'm gonna be right back.

20:55.586 --> 20:56.644
All right.

20:57.154 --> 20:59.782
Yeah, you got the one
on the left.

20:59.857 --> 21:01.620
Look here,
let me do the talking.

21:30.454 --> 21:31.978
Don't go inside that place.

21:32.056 --> 21:33.489
You know what Mama said.

21:33.557 --> 21:36.025
Go home
and don't tell Mama nothin'.

21:36.560 --> 21:37.925
Go, George.

21:42.400 --> 21:44.231
George, get out of here!

22:09.994 --> 22:12.827
Hey, boy,
who let you in?

22:13.064 --> 22:15.191
You must be
Aretha's son, huh?

22:15.266 --> 22:17.496
Yes, sir.
Ray Charles Robinson.

22:17.968 --> 22:20.698
I've been seeing you
sneakin' around here.

22:21.038 --> 22:22.733
You like the piano, huh?

22:23.307 --> 22:25.332
Come on, you want
to learn how to play?

22:25.409 --> 22:26.706
Come on over here.

22:26.777 --> 22:28.506
Let me show you how to play.
Come on.

22:28.579 --> 22:30.809
I'm gonna teach you
how to play.

22:30.881 --> 22:33.816
What we'll do, I'm gonna teach
you three notes, right?

22:33.884 --> 22:35.977
This is the first note,
right here.

22:37.555 --> 22:38.647
Play that.

22:39.924 --> 22:42.154
And here's the second note,
right here.

22:43.327 --> 22:44.555
Play that.

22:46.263 --> 22:47.924
Here's the third note.

22:50.968 --> 22:52.265
Now, here's the way
it goes.

22:52.336 --> 22:53.928
Listen.
Listen closely, now.

22:57.675 --> 22:59.006
Play that.

23:00.578 --> 23:01.909
Good!

23:03.080 --> 23:04.843
Try the other notes.

23:13.691 --> 23:15.158
Every club we hit,

23:15.226 --> 23:17.694
it's your responsibility
to rehearse the band.

23:17.795 --> 23:19.820
These are some
lazy-ass bastards,

23:19.897 --> 23:22.195
so you gotta make sure
that they don't slough off.

23:22.600 --> 23:24.727
You gotta be ready
and dressed to open the show.

23:24.802 --> 23:27.168
Now, Lowell likes to take
a nap before he goes on.

23:27.238 --> 23:30.298
You just do your thing
until he feels like
comin' out.

23:30.374 --> 23:33.275
And when Lowell's playin',
you keep the band sharp.

23:33.344 --> 23:34.333
Uh... uh, just one thing.

23:34.412 --> 23:35.344
What?

23:35.413 --> 23:38.007
Did Jack tell you that
I have to be paid in singles?

23:38.082 --> 23:40.482
You just do your job,
you're gonna get your money.

23:41.085 --> 23:43.451
# Baby, come on, down #

23:43.521 --> 23:46.684
# Your daddy's
in the heart of town #

23:50.428 --> 23:51.918
# Come on down #

23:51.996 --> 23:55.454
# Your daddy's
in the heart of town #

24:01.705 --> 24:04.037
How'd you get the name
Fathead anyway?

24:04.108 --> 24:05.598
Why do they call me
Fathead?

24:05.743 --> 24:07.267
Nah, you don't want to hear.

24:07.344 --> 24:09.335
But this is what
I really want to know.

24:09.413 --> 24:11.472
Do any of you
fine young ladies know

24:11.549 --> 24:13.915
where we can get a nice steak
this time of night?

24:13.984 --> 24:17.010
You mean something big,
thick, and juicy?

24:17.087 --> 24:18.884
Oh, yeah,
that's just what I mean.

24:20.124 --> 24:22.388
Fathead, where you guys
headed, man?

24:22.960 --> 24:25.053
I ain't babysittin'
no blind cat.

24:26.063 --> 24:27.462
Uh, I'm sorry, Ray,

24:27.531 --> 24:30.261
but, uh, the law says
there's only six to a cab.

24:30.334 --> 24:32.359
Come on, ladies,
let's get out of here.

25:29.093 --> 25:31.288
# Everyday #

25:36.467 --> 25:40.130
# Everyday I have the blues #

25:46.610 --> 25:49.977
# Everyday, everyday #

25:54.285 --> 25:56.583
Pay up, baby!
Yeah, that's all right.

25:56.654 --> 25:58.918
I been shootin' craps
since I was 12 years old.

25:58.989 --> 26:01.549
Don't never shoot craps
on a white woman's grave.

26:01.625 --> 26:02.614
Why not?

26:02.693 --> 26:03.751
It's bad luck.

26:03.827 --> 26:07.228
<i># You know bad luck
and trouble, people #</i>

26:10.601 --> 26:13.263
# Well, you know
I had my share #

26:19.577 --> 26:21.272
That's for being
late to the bus.

26:21.345 --> 26:22.835
Wilbur,
you a low-down piece...

26:22.913 --> 26:24.380
You better move on.

26:29.853 --> 26:32.014
Ah, Mr. One-dollar Bill.

26:33.057 --> 26:36.720
$5, $10, $15, $20...

26:37.828 --> 26:40.490
Now, you like to start
counting that again?

26:41.699 --> 26:43.530
All right, damn you.

26:45.869 --> 26:48.030
$284, $285...

26:48.105 --> 26:50.938
Listen, man, I ain't
no damn seein'- eye dog.

26:51.008 --> 26:54.444
<i># You know
ain't nobody worried
about me #</i>

26:56.013 --> 27:00.712
# I don't see nobody,
nobody cryin' ##

27:07.691 --> 27:10.159
Fathead, open up. Open up.
I got to take a leak.

27:13.163 --> 27:15.961
Hey, what you doing, man?
Close the door, Fat!

27:16.200 --> 27:18.498
Say, Ray, we'll be in here
for a little while.

27:18.569 --> 27:21.367
Use the women's can,
down there on your right.

27:21.438 --> 27:22.996
I don't want to use
the women's can.

27:23.073 --> 27:24.097
This way.

27:43.894 --> 27:45.225
Oh, God!

27:46.163 --> 27:48.028
Say, Ray,
you all right?

27:49.199 --> 27:50.928
Yeah, I must have slipped
on the wet.

27:51.001 --> 27:52.093
There's a pipe broke.

27:52.169 --> 27:53.727
There's water everywhere.
You see it?

27:53.804 --> 27:55.704
Let's go, man.
Close the door.

27:55.773 --> 27:57.172
All right,
quit playing, Ray.

27:57.241 --> 27:59.732
We'll be in here a while.
Now go on now!

28:07.451 --> 28:08.475
Where you from, Ray?

28:08.552 --> 28:09.780
North Florida.

28:10.187 --> 28:11.677
Oh, North Florida boy.

28:12.222 --> 28:13.382
Your people
still down there?

28:13.524 --> 28:14.684
No.

28:15.893 --> 28:17.019
All right.

28:17.528 --> 28:19.052
Hey, uh, pardon me
for askin',

28:19.129 --> 28:21.029
but how do you
get around so good

28:21.098 --> 28:22.998
without a cane
or a dog?

28:23.767 --> 28:26.668
How do you get around so good
without a cane or dog?

28:27.271 --> 28:28.863
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to pry.

28:30.941 --> 28:33.034
My ears got to be
my eyes, man. Its...

28:33.844 --> 28:35.106
Everything sounds different.

28:35.179 --> 28:37.238
You know that's why
I wear hard-soled shoes,

28:37.314 --> 28:39.305
so I can hear my footsteps
echo off the wall.

28:39.383 --> 28:42.614
So when I pass by
an open doorway,
the sound changes.

28:42.720 --> 28:44.119
Wow. That's cool.

28:44.588 --> 28:48.183
You know you got to learn
pretty quick if you want
to get around on your own.

28:48.258 --> 28:49.384
Yeah.

28:50.027 --> 28:52.291
You know, during the war,
there was a whole lot

28:52.362 --> 28:54.557
I had to learn fast,
or I wouldn't be here.

28:57.134 --> 28:59.534
Seein' that much death
ain't natural.

29:01.405 --> 29:03.737
Yeah, seein' death
ain't natural.

29:08.212 --> 29:10.203
Boys, get from
'round that still.

29:10.280 --> 29:11.679
Y'all know
better than that.

29:11.749 --> 29:13.182
Come on, catch me.

29:18.522 --> 29:20.717
Stay from 'round this fire
and get clean.

29:20.791 --> 29:22.383
Dinner will be ready soon.

29:22.459 --> 29:23.949
Hear me, Ray?

29:25.729 --> 29:26.991
I got you.
I got you.

29:27.064 --> 29:28.429
No, you didn't.
You missed me.

29:28.499 --> 29:29.796
Stop cheatin', Ray.

29:29.867 --> 29:32.495
Okay, you got me.

29:32.569 --> 29:34.298
But I got you back.

29:34.371 --> 29:36.100
I'm not playin' no more.

29:36.340 --> 29:37.534
Sissy!

29:39.243 --> 29:41.609
Come on, Ray.
Let's go swimmin'.

29:43.781 --> 29:46.306
Let's go swim
in Mama's washtub.

29:47.317 --> 29:49.444
Ray, come on, Ray,
play with me.

29:49.720 --> 29:51.813
You better get down
before Mama sees you.

29:51.889 --> 29:53.356
I'm a giant!

29:57.494 --> 29:58.961
Some giant.

30:00.030 --> 30:02.828
Come on, George.
I ain't playin' this game.

30:03.867 --> 30:05.391
That ain't funny.

30:07.337 --> 30:09.999
Boys, I got some field peas
and rice cooking.

30:10.073 --> 30:12.667
And there's that smothered
corn left from yesterday.

30:12.743 --> 30:16.736
And if you're real good,
I might have two pieces
of peach cobbler.

30:17.481 --> 30:20.177
Ray, didn't I tell you
to get in this house?

30:23.587 --> 30:25.179
Dear God, no!

30:29.927 --> 30:31.121
That's Aretha's boy!

30:31.261 --> 30:32.592
Breathe, baby, breathe.

30:32.663 --> 30:36.064
Just breathe, baby, breathe.
Let it out!

30:36.133 --> 30:37.930
Let it out, please!

30:38.068 --> 30:39.433
Breathe for your mama, now.

30:39.503 --> 30:40.834
Come on, George.

30:41.071 --> 30:43.198
Why didn't you do somethin'?

30:43.707 --> 30:45.140
Why didn't you call me?

30:46.710 --> 30:48.371
Help us, Lord!

30:48.445 --> 30:50.072
The Lord done took him home.

30:59.690 --> 31:00.918
All right.

31:01.525 --> 31:03.755
Food and piss stop.
Open it up.

31:07.064 --> 31:09.760
The food is hot.
You've got 45 minutes.

31:10.200 --> 31:12.225
I could eat a horse.
Where's it?

31:12.369 --> 31:14.394
Follow your nose.
Right over there.

31:15.105 --> 31:16.231
Wilbur.

31:16.306 --> 31:17.364
What?

31:17.441 --> 31:19.739
45 minutes
ain't enough time.

31:19.810 --> 31:21.300
We need more
than that, Jack.

31:21.378 --> 31:22.970
Not to eat,
you don't.

31:23.046 --> 31:25.139
Now if you got other business,
you better choose,

31:25.215 --> 31:26.739
because this bus
is rollin' on time.

31:26.817 --> 31:30.048
Come on, Mercedes got
a washroom in the back.

31:30.387 --> 31:32.947
And you,
you can smell it.

31:34.625 --> 31:35.649
Jeff.

31:35.726 --> 31:36.715
Yes, sir?

31:36.793 --> 31:38.055
Uh, could you help me
in there?

31:38.128 --> 31:39.527
Sure thing, Ray.

31:39.596 --> 31:40.620
Hey, Mercedes.

31:40.697 --> 31:43.495
Hey, baby.
I hope you wiped your feet
before you came in here.

31:43.567 --> 31:45.000
There you go. Come on.
Take that.

31:45.068 --> 31:46.933
The bathroom's right there
in front of you.

31:47.004 --> 31:47.971
Okay.

31:48.038 --> 31:49.300
You want me
to fix you a plate?

31:49.373 --> 31:50.670
Uh, no, I'm... I'm fine.

31:50.974 --> 31:52.134
All right.

31:52.209 --> 31:54.074
Sweet potato pie it is.

31:55.512 --> 31:56.638
Whoo, let's go, man.

31:56.713 --> 31:58.476
That was a long
bus ride, wasn't it?

31:58.548 --> 31:59.640
Oh, come on, man.

31:59.716 --> 32:02.810
Hey, man!
The can's down the hall.

32:02.886 --> 32:04.751
I know where the can is.
What y'all doing?

32:04.821 --> 32:06.448
Do yourself a favor
and leave.

32:06.523 --> 32:08.388
I'll leave when
I'm gettin' ready to leave.

32:08.458 --> 32:09.982
Come on, Fathead,
I want in.

32:10.060 --> 32:11.755
This ain't no weed, Ray.

32:11.895 --> 32:13.829
And we ain't
snorting no bitch.

32:13.897 --> 32:15.125
This is boy.

32:15.198 --> 32:17.666
Boy'll make your ass
null and void.

32:17.734 --> 32:19.326
So get on out of here, man.

32:19.403 --> 32:21.234
Null and void,
just like my life.

32:21.305 --> 32:22.932
I'll be right at home.

32:23.006 --> 32:24.701
Look, I ain't gonna
wait all night.

32:24.808 --> 32:26.469
Hell, it's his funeral, man.

32:28.545 --> 32:30.570
Ray, let's go get
something to eat.

32:30.647 --> 32:32.239
I'll leave
when I get a taste.

32:32.316 --> 32:33.510
Ray, what you gonna do, man?

32:33.583 --> 32:35.016
This train's pullin' out,
brother.

32:35.085 --> 32:36.916
I ain't having nothin'
to do with this.

32:36.987 --> 32:38.682
I warned you, Ray.
Come on, man.

32:38.755 --> 32:39.949
I been warned.

32:40.023 --> 32:41.285
Sit down, Ray. Right there.

32:41.358 --> 32:42.882
I'm gonna take you
on a little ride.

32:42.960 --> 32:45.622
It'll cost you, though.
You got some cash?

32:45.696 --> 32:47.129
Will this do?

32:47.898 --> 32:48.887
That'll do.

32:51.134 --> 32:52.999
Where you been?
Where them other fools?

32:53.070 --> 32:54.537
Come on,
get it while it's hot!

32:55.906 --> 32:58.238
You're going to feel
a little pinch.

33:00.911 --> 33:02.503
I ain't givin'
up on you, boy.

33:03.947 --> 33:05.471
Feel it, baby?

33:06.650 --> 33:08.447
Just take the ride.

33:09.586 --> 33:11.417
It's better than sex.

33:11.788 --> 33:14.120
There ain't nothin'
better than sex.

33:19.563 --> 33:21.656
<i># We will walk #</i>

33:21.732 --> 33:26.669
# through the streets
of the city #

33:27.270 --> 33:28.897
# Of the city #

33:29.740 --> 33:33.198
# Where our loved ones #

33:33.276 --> 33:38.213
# have gone on before #

33:40.884 --> 33:45.548
# We will stand on the banks #

33:46.223 --> 33:49.522
# of the river #

33:49.626 --> 33:51.526
# Of the river #

33:51.895 --> 33:54.887
# Where we'll meet #

33:55.065 --> 34:00.002
# to part no more #

34:03.306 --> 34:05.467
# I pray #

34:05.542 --> 34:06.600
# I pray #

34:06.676 --> 34:09.338
# Be free from now on #

34:09.446 --> 34:11.937
# Pray to you, Lord #

34:12.014 --> 34:16.918
# Where our true ones
have gone #

34:17.621 --> 34:20.317
# Gone before #

34:20.389 --> 34:22.324
# Gone before #

34:23.025 --> 34:27.588
# We will stand on the banks #

34:28.364 --> 34:31.697
# of the river #

34:33.770 --> 34:36.431
# Where we'll meet #

34:36.505 --> 34:41.136
# to part no more ##

35:11.374 --> 35:14.400
Ray, come on, let me put
this salve on I got
from Dr. McLeod.

35:14.478 --> 35:16.002
No, I don't like it.
It stings.

35:16.079 --> 35:17.546
Boy, get up here.

35:18.115 --> 35:21.016
I paid a whole dollar for it.
It better work.

35:21.118 --> 35:23.586
Now hold up your head,
like the doctor says.

35:23.653 --> 35:25.621
This is gonna
make you feel better.

35:30.026 --> 35:32.221
Ray, come on in
for dinner.

35:32.295 --> 35:34.593
And stop rubbin' those eyes.

35:46.543 --> 35:48.568
Ray, I won't beat around
the bush with you.

35:48.645 --> 35:49.907
You're goin' blind.

35:49.980 --> 35:53.347
The doctor's sayin'
there's nothing they can do,
so we got to do it ourselves.

35:53.416 --> 35:54.474
Yes, ma'am, I know, but...

35:54.551 --> 35:55.518
Stop it.

35:55.585 --> 35:57.143
Stop it right now.

35:57.220 --> 35:59.154
We ain't got no time
for no tears.

35:59.222 --> 36:00.883
Ain't nobody gonna
have no pity on you

36:00.957 --> 36:02.254
just 'cause
you're goin' blind.

36:02.325 --> 36:03.485
Now wipe them eyes.

36:03.560 --> 36:04.959
Yes, ma'am.

36:06.963 --> 36:09.261
Okay, I'll show you
how to do something once.

36:09.332 --> 36:10.959
I'll help you
if you mess up twice.

36:11.034 --> 36:12.729
But the third time,
you're on your own,

36:12.802 --> 36:15.168
'cause that's the way
it is in the world.

36:15.238 --> 36:16.728
All right,
now get up.

36:18.575 --> 36:21.806
Remember, you goin' blind,
but you ain't stupid.

36:23.914 --> 36:25.472
Remember how many stairs
there were?

36:25.549 --> 36:26.880
Four.

36:26.950 --> 36:30.442
Good. You're gonna
have to learn
how to use your memory.

36:30.520 --> 36:31.680
Now turn around.

36:31.755 --> 36:33.689
I want you
to hold out your hands,

36:33.757 --> 36:36.692
and use them as your eyes,
and find the door.

36:37.894 --> 36:40.920
Good.
That's real good, baby.

36:51.241 --> 36:52.230
Hi.

36:59.082 --> 37:02.813
# Baby,
let me hold your hand #

37:07.057 --> 37:10.823
# Till I make you understand #

37:12.696 --> 37:14.960
# Oh, baby #

37:18.535 --> 37:21.561
# Let me hold your hand #

37:29.212 --> 37:31.840
# I really true believe #

37:31.915 --> 37:35.578
This fool makes one record,
and you'd think he's
the star of the band.

37:35.652 --> 37:38.485
Well, he's got somethin',
ain't he?

37:39.089 --> 37:40.954
His wax won't
even hit the charts.

37:41.625 --> 37:43.490
You're still the man.

37:45.095 --> 37:47.461
# I want you to know #

37:49.733 --> 37:51.030
# I'm in love ##

37:51.101 --> 37:52.090
She wasn't that fine.

37:52.168 --> 37:53.567
There's somethin'
wrong with you.

37:53.637 --> 37:56.970
No, man, she's fine.
She's fine.
You leave her alone.

37:57.540 --> 37:58.507
Look at Ray.

37:59.442 --> 38:00.568
You see that?

38:00.644 --> 38:02.305
He feels her wrist
'cause he figures

38:02.379 --> 38:04.677
that's the way to tell
if she's good-looking or not.

38:04.748 --> 38:07.182
You know I had my eye on you
all night long.

38:07.250 --> 38:09.241
Oh, he right this time.

38:11.221 --> 38:14.190
See what a little fame does
to Null and Void?

38:14.557 --> 38:17.720
Anybody see that
fine-looking gal
in the yellow dress?

38:19.296 --> 38:20.422
You hear this man?

38:20.497 --> 38:21.987
You snooze, you lose.

38:22.065 --> 38:23.794
We gonna dock your pay, man.

38:23.867 --> 38:25.801
That's $2 off of your busride.

38:30.607 --> 38:34.099
<i># Baby,
I want you by my side #</i>

38:37.013 --> 38:38.275
<i># I do #</i>

38:41.985 --> 38:44.579
<i># I want you to know #</i>

38:46.856 --> 38:50.348
<i># Our love
we will never hide #</i>

38:51.661 --> 38:53.959
<i># Oh, no, no, no ##</i>

38:55.765 --> 38:57.426
All right, who's next?

38:58.401 --> 38:59.834
It's a shame, Jimmy.

38:59.903 --> 39:01.894
You're just gonna
piss this right up your arm.

39:01.971 --> 39:04.531
You don't tell me
what to do with my money.

39:04.908 --> 39:08.537
All right, come on. Step up.
The $1 sensation.

39:13.783 --> 39:15.580
You wanna keep counting?

39:15.652 --> 39:17.381
What's the matter with you,
boy?

39:17.454 --> 39:18.853
$50 ain't good enough for you?

39:18.922 --> 39:21.015
That ain't $50. Keep counting.

39:21.591 --> 39:24.924
I guess you want charity,
since that record
of yours ain't selling.

39:27.997 --> 39:29.464
Get him off my back!

39:34.270 --> 39:35.931
Break it up!

39:36.072 --> 39:37.733
What the hell's
going on in here?

39:38.274 --> 39:41.141
The blind sensation don't like
the money I'm trying
to pay him!

39:41.211 --> 39:42.269
He's cheating me! I quit!

39:42.345 --> 39:44.006
Oh, you lying son of a bitch!

39:44.314 --> 39:46.407
Don't be fighting nobody
that can see!

39:46.483 --> 39:49.213
Listen, I ain't
runnnin' around lookin' for
singles for this chump!

39:49.285 --> 39:50.377
There's $50 here, Ray.

39:50.453 --> 39:51.442
You see that, fool?

39:51.521 --> 39:54.354
Shut up, Wilbur!
Ray, from now on,
I'll handle your pay myself.

39:54.424 --> 39:55.413
I'm tired of this!

39:55.492 --> 39:57.221
I'll tell Jack to
find you somebody else!

39:57.293 --> 39:58.521
You sure?
It's cold out there.

39:58.595 --> 40:00.620
Don't worry about me,
I can take care of myself.

40:00.697 --> 40:02.858
Ray!
Damn it, Wilbur!

40:02.932 --> 40:03.956
Let him go!

40:04.033 --> 40:05.523
What we gonna do now?

40:13.343 --> 40:17.040
"After the death of Moses, the
Lord spake unto Joshua saying:

40:17.113 --> 40:19.513
"'Moses my servant is dead.

40:19.582 --> 40:22.050
"'Now therefore arise.
Go over to Jordan.

40:22.118 --> 40:23.244
"'Be not afraid,

40:23.319 --> 40:25.412
For the Lord thy God
is with thee. "'

40:25.488 --> 40:26.955
Mr. Charles.

40:27.457 --> 40:28.822
Who is it?

40:28.925 --> 40:30.586
Mr. Charles,
my name is Ahmet Ertegun.

40:30.660 --> 40:32.252
May I have
a moment of your time?

40:35.999 --> 40:37.899
What do you want, man?
I'm at church.

40:37.967 --> 40:40.265
I'm sorry.
I'll come back later.

40:40.403 --> 40:42.462
You're here now.
What do you want?

40:43.740 --> 40:45.867
My company, Atlantic Records,
has acquired

40:45.942 --> 40:48.103
your contract
from Swing Time.

40:48.611 --> 40:50.340
I'd like
to discuss your future.

40:50.413 --> 40:53.246
Hold on. Don't jive me now.
I ain't for sale.

40:53.483 --> 40:54.973
May I sit down?

40:57.620 --> 40:59.588
You see, Mr. Charles,

41:00.290 --> 41:02.417
Jack Lauderdale
has found himself,

41:02.559 --> 41:04.686
shall we say,
a little overextended,

41:05.128 --> 41:07.926
and has had to
unload some of his talent.

41:07.997 --> 41:09.965
When your name
came up, I jumped at

41:10.033 --> 41:11.967
the chance to work with you.
I'm a big fan.

41:12.035 --> 41:13.935
What if I want to go
to another company?

41:14.003 --> 41:16.437
There's a guy out there
right now that is willing
to pay me

41:16.506 --> 41:18.872
seven cents a record.
Can you do that?

41:19.242 --> 41:22.040
Man, I could promise you
15 cents a record,

41:22.879 --> 41:26.315
but you won't get it
any more than
he'll pay you seven.

41:28.051 --> 41:31.214
What I will do
is promise you
five cents a record

41:31.387 --> 41:33.685
and pay you five cents
a record.

41:34.457 --> 41:37.722
If you think pennies,
Mr. Charles, you get pennies.

41:38.595 --> 41:40.324
You think dollars,

41:41.331 --> 41:42.923
you get dollars.

41:44.901 --> 41:47.665
I like how you put
things together, man.

41:48.171 --> 41:49.661
Ahem, you know what?

41:50.173 --> 41:52.698
Omelet,
you're all right with me.

41:53.109 --> 41:54.303
Ahmet.
Ahmet.

41:54.377 --> 41:55.537
What kind of name is that?

41:55.612 --> 41:56.840
I'm Turkish.

41:56.946 --> 41:58.140
Well, you know what?

41:58.214 --> 42:01.115
I guess
Jack Lauderdale's bad luck
is my good fortune.

42:01.251 --> 42:04.311
I knew that Atlantic Records
was bigger than Swing Time.

42:04.387 --> 42:06.947
You guys do good music.
I dig Atlantic.

42:07.023 --> 42:08.490
You could have fooled me.

42:08.558 --> 42:11.254
Well, you know,
I gotta keep my eye
on you city boys.

42:11.828 --> 42:13.659
Down home,
we call it "country dumb."

42:15.765 --> 42:17.630
Hey, man, it ain't Turkish.

42:22.672 --> 42:24.970
# Went to see my sweetheart #

42:25.875 --> 42:28.639
# Last night around
about ten #

42:29.212 --> 42:32.579
# She said, move, sweet papa #

42:33.416 --> 42:35.941
# Squeeze me
every now and then #

42:36.185 --> 42:37.914
What do you think?

42:37.987 --> 42:40.387
Man, nobody wants
another Nat King Cole.

42:41.558 --> 42:43.526
# 'Cause she sleep that way #

42:43.593 --> 42:46.619
# The midnight hour #

42:47.864 --> 42:50.458
# Has found me lonely #

42:51.701 --> 42:53.601
# So unhappy #

42:54.904 --> 42:56.667
# As I can be #

42:56.839 --> 42:59.706
Ahmet, it's just
like Charles Brown.

43:01.911 --> 43:04.345
Okay, I'll talk to him.

43:06.950 --> 43:09.817
All right, fellas,
that's a cut.
That's a cut, fellas.

43:10.453 --> 43:11.715
Fellas!

43:11.788 --> 43:13.119
<i>Band can take five.</i>

43:13.256 --> 43:14.587
He just don't get it.

43:14.657 --> 43:17.649
You either sound original,
or you got nothin'.

43:17.760 --> 43:19.955
Ahmet,
what'd you think of that?

43:20.096 --> 43:23.259
Ray, I want to tell you
something, and I don't want
you to take it wrong.

43:23.333 --> 43:24.664
Then give it to me right.

43:24.734 --> 43:28.135
I signed you
because I sensed
something special in you

43:28.204 --> 43:31.401
not because you sound like
Nat Cole or Charles Brown.

43:31.474 --> 43:33.305
I thought you like what I do.

43:33.376 --> 43:35.310
We... we love the timbre
of your voice,

43:35.378 --> 43:37.608
we like your virtuosity,
your energy...

43:37.680 --> 43:38.942
But not my music.

43:39.015 --> 43:40.448
Come on, man,
I didn't say that.

43:40.950 --> 43:42.975
Ahmet, this is what I do, man.

43:43.052 --> 43:45.179
I gotta make a living.
This is what the people want.

43:45.254 --> 43:46.846
I don't know no other way.

43:46.923 --> 43:48.652
We got to help you find one.

43:48.725 --> 43:51.057
Look, let's try a little
change of pace, okay?

43:51.127 --> 43:52.526
You're familiar
with stride piano?

43:52.595 --> 43:55.894
You kidding me, man?
The man who I learned the
piano from is a stride player.

43:55.965 --> 43:58.991
<i>Okay, I got a song.
It's called The Mess Around.</i>

43:59.068 --> 44:00.899
<i>The Mess Around.
Cute title. Who wrote it?</i>

44:00.970 --> 44:02.369
I did.

44:02.605 --> 44:04.038
Ah, you wrote it.

44:04.107 --> 44:05.096
Yeah.

44:05.508 --> 44:06.873
Well, sing it to me, man.

44:07.143 --> 44:08.303
Sing it?
Yeah.

44:08.378 --> 44:10.039
It ain't like
I can read the lyrics.

44:10.113 --> 44:12.707
Okay.
Well, it's the key of G.

44:12.782 --> 44:14.215
Okay. Key of G.

44:15.351 --> 44:16.340
Uh-huh.

44:17.153 --> 44:18.142
Yeah.

44:18.321 --> 44:21.154
Yeah, but it's a kind of
Pete Johnson thing.

44:21.257 --> 44:22.622
Pete Johnson.

44:24.427 --> 44:26.088
Yeah, yeah, that's it.

44:26.195 --> 44:28.254
You like that?
Here we go. Two, three, four.

44:28.331 --> 44:31.630
# You can talk
about the pit barbecue #

44:31.701 --> 44:33.931
# The band was jumpin',
the people, too #

44:34.003 --> 44:35.994
# They're doin'
the mess around #

44:36.839 --> 44:38.864
# They're doin'
the mess around #

44:39.742 --> 44:41.676
# They're doin'
the mess around #

44:41.744 --> 44:43.735
# Everybody doin'
the mess around ##

44:43.813 --> 44:45.974
All right, that's good.
Let me take it from here.

44:46.049 --> 44:49.610
# Now this band's gonna
play from nine to one #

44:49.686 --> 44:52.280
# Everybody here's gonna
have some fun #

44:52.388 --> 44:54.151
# Doin' the mess around #

44:54.924 --> 44:57.154
# Ah, doin' the mess around #

44:58.761 --> 45:00.956
# They doin' the mess around #

45:01.064 --> 45:03.157
# Everybody doin'
the mess around #

45:05.301 --> 45:08.737
# Now you see that girl
with that diamond ring #

45:09.372 --> 45:12.170
# She knows
how to shake that thing #

45:12.642 --> 45:14.166
# Mess around #

45:14.744 --> 45:16.712
# I declare
she can mess around #

45:18.314 --> 45:20.043
# Ah, mess around #

45:20.450 --> 45:22.816
# Everybody do
the mess around ##

45:28.891 --> 45:30.415
Now we got something!

45:30.493 --> 45:31.983
That's all right there.

45:33.496 --> 45:34.758
What do you think, Ahmet?

45:34.831 --> 45:35.855
Great, Ray!

45:35.932 --> 45:37.058
Unbelievable!

45:37.133 --> 45:38.225
Who's that?

45:39.235 --> 45:41.430
Ray, I want you to meet
my new partner, Jerry.

45:41.537 --> 45:43.095
Mr. Ray Charles,
Jerry Wexler.

45:43.172 --> 45:44.161
Hey.

45:44.240 --> 45:47.300
Don't worry, Ray.
I'm going to step back,
I'm gonna watch,

45:47.376 --> 45:49.776
I'm gonna learn
how to produce a record.
I'm in awe.

45:49.846 --> 45:51.074
That was out of sight.

45:51.147 --> 45:52.944
That's some running
and riffing, man!

45:53.249 --> 45:54.944
Well,
this'll make you shout, man.

46:03.059 --> 46:05.823
<i>We're listening to that
new recording, Mess Around</i>

46:05.895 --> 46:08.193
<i>by Atlantic recording artist,
Ray Charles.</i>

46:08.264 --> 46:11.756
<i>And we have the gentleman
live here in the KCOH studios.</i>

46:11.834 --> 46:14.894
So, Ray, when you're not
making your own music,
what do you listen to?

46:14.971 --> 46:18.634
You know what, the fact is,
King Bee, I really
and truly love gospel.

46:18.708 --> 46:21.609
One of my favorite groups
is from right here in Houston:

46:21.677 --> 46:23.542
The Cecil Shaw Singers.

46:23.746 --> 46:27.273
You heard it:
Ray Charles endorses
Houston's own Cecil Shaw.

46:27.350 --> 46:29.284
We'll be playing
gospel all day Sunday

46:29.352 --> 46:31.047
but right now,
let's hear some more

46:31.120 --> 46:32.747
<i>of that Mess Around
by Ray Charles.</i>

46:32.822 --> 46:34.153
<i>K.B., line 1.</i>

46:36.526 --> 46:37.891
King Bee.

46:39.595 --> 46:40.584
Mmm-hmm.

46:41.597 --> 46:43.258
Yeah, he's right here.

46:43.900 --> 46:46.460
Miss Della Antwine
of the Cecil Shaw Singers.

46:49.939 --> 46:51.770
Hello, Miss Antwine.

46:52.175 --> 46:54.939
<i>You sung tenor in
Jesus Is My Shepherd, right?</i>

46:55.011 --> 46:56.239
Yes.

46:57.046 --> 46:58.809
How did you pick me out?

46:58.881 --> 47:01.873
Actually,
I... I hear like you see.

47:02.618 --> 47:05.678
Like that hummingbird
outside the window,
for instance.

47:11.861 --> 47:13.123
I can't hear her.

47:13.196 --> 47:14.458
You have to listen.

47:32.515 --> 47:33.573
Yes.

47:33.649 --> 47:34.638
Yeah.

47:34.917 --> 47:36.077
Yes, you can.

47:36.152 --> 47:37.176
OH-OH.

47:37.253 --> 47:38.242
You hear that?

47:38.321 --> 47:39.345
What?

47:40.089 --> 47:42.250
Her heart just
skipped a beat.

47:44.493 --> 47:46.358
Oh, did you like my record?

47:46.662 --> 47:49.028
The one that King Bee
was playin'?

47:50.466 --> 47:52.093
It was very nice.

47:52.335 --> 47:54.530
Different than the others.

47:55.104 --> 47:57.038
I've heard
a lot of your music.

47:57.106 --> 47:58.664
Was it very nice, too?

47:58.741 --> 48:01.005
Look, Miss Antwine, if you
don't really like the record,

48:01.077 --> 48:04.478
you ain't got to
beat around the bush with me.
I mean, my mama never did.

48:04.547 --> 48:06.845
It's not that I don't
enjoy your music.

48:06.916 --> 48:09.248
It's just that I feel
I've heard it before.

48:09.318 --> 48:11.843
I keep wondering
what the real Ray Charles
sound like.

48:11.921 --> 48:13.411
Ray Charles? Who's he?

48:13.489 --> 48:15.389
Nobody,
if you don't know.

48:15.458 --> 48:16.447
Huh?

48:17.260 --> 48:19.728
Sorry. I should have
kept my mouth shut.

48:19.795 --> 48:21.990
Oh, no, no.
Then you wouldn't be you.

48:23.199 --> 48:25.599
You know, it's not
like I haven't heard
that before.

48:25.668 --> 48:29.001
I guess I just, uh, never
really listened, that's all.

48:31.207 --> 48:34.176
Ain't nobody ever put
it that sweet, I guess.

48:51.394 --> 48:53.294
You know what,
Miss Della Bea Antwine?

48:53.362 --> 48:55.489
You really are a country girl.
You know that?

48:55.564 --> 48:57.532
Yes.
How'd you know?

48:57.600 --> 48:59.659
I could tell by
the way you ordered.

48:59.735 --> 49:01.896
"Let me get molasses
with my cornbread."

49:03.139 --> 49:04.834
Were you raised
on a farm?

49:04.907 --> 49:07.740
My mother did
a little sharecropping
in Florida.

49:07.810 --> 49:09.300
Is she still there?

49:09.378 --> 49:12.211
God bless her heart,
she passed away
when I went to school.

49:12.281 --> 49:13.771
Ray, I'm sorry.

49:14.250 --> 49:15.945
She never was
real healthy.

49:16.018 --> 49:18.578
She just worked
herself to death,
poor thing.

49:18.688 --> 49:21.452
That's why she didn't
want me carrying around
no tin cup.

49:21.524 --> 49:23.253
The kids
I went to school with,

49:23.326 --> 49:26.022
they were doing basket-weavin'
and wickerwork.

49:26.896 --> 49:29.194
But not you.
Because of your gift.

49:29.298 --> 49:30.925
Because of my ears.

49:31.233 --> 49:33.133
See, I can mimic
damn near anybody,

49:33.202 --> 49:35.898
and I... I... I... I make
a pretty decent
living at it.

49:35.972 --> 49:38.031
It's just, if I
change my style up

49:38.107 --> 49:39.631
and people
really don't dig it,

49:39.709 --> 49:41.973
I mean, what am I
left with, you know?

49:42.211 --> 49:44.577
I mean, when you're blind,
Miss Antwine,

49:44.714 --> 49:46.807
you ain't got
that many choices.

49:48.050 --> 49:50.541
Seem to me
like you got all
the choices in the world.

49:51.721 --> 49:53.518
God gave you
the gift to sound

49:53.589 --> 49:55.887
like anybody you please,
even yourself.

49:57.626 --> 49:59.821
We're here.
This is where I live.

50:00.963 --> 50:02.794
Well, you think
the preacher'd let me in?

50:02.865 --> 50:05.197
I mean, uh, I'm a sinner,
but I need a little prayer.

50:05.267 --> 50:07.758
His wife don't like
me having male company.

50:07.870 --> 50:10.998
Well, tell him there's
a soul out here
that needs savin'.

50:11.774 --> 50:15.175
You know what, Miss Antwine,
you really got me thinkin'.

50:17.013 --> 50:18.480
About what?

50:18.581 --> 50:21.914
About my life.
About my music.

50:24.020 --> 50:25.510
About everything.

50:27.757 --> 50:31.249
Ray, don't... don't you think
we're movin' a little fast?

50:33.195 --> 50:34.958
Listen, I'm... I'm gonna
go to New York

50:35.031 --> 50:37.522
for a couple of weeks,
and when I get back,

50:37.933 --> 50:40.401
you can take it as
slow as you want.

50:43.072 --> 50:44.903
All right, Mr. Charles.

50:46.275 --> 50:48.038
All right, Miss Antwine.

50:48.444 --> 50:50.071
I'll see you
in a couple of weeks.

50:50.146 --> 50:52.171
Well, hold on, now.
Let me call you a cab.

50:52.248 --> 50:53.943
I got it. Three blocks up,

50:54.016 --> 50:56.712
left for two, right for one.

50:56.819 --> 50:58.514
Fifteen giant steps,

50:58.587 --> 51:00.521
and I'm at the
Crystal White Hotel. Hello.

51:07.763 --> 51:10.357
<i>Mess Around was
a positive step for us, Ray.</i>

51:10.433 --> 51:11.559
<i>We're making progress.</i>

51:11.634 --> 51:13.795
Oh, come on, Ahmet.
Now, you've been nice to me.

51:13.869 --> 51:15.632
But I haven't given
you guys any hits.

51:15.704 --> 51:17.262
Atlantic Records
has been good to me,

51:17.339 --> 51:19.034
but if you want me to do
something special,

51:19.108 --> 51:20.473
I'm gonna need my own band.

51:20.943 --> 51:24.174
Oh, man. Taking a band
out on the road
costs a mint, Ray.

51:24.246 --> 51:27.306
I mean, even Joe Morris
is struggling. His band's
had a hit record.

51:27.383 --> 51:29.214
But, Ahmet, listen,
I'm not Joe Morris.

51:29.285 --> 51:31.549
Man, you told me if I think
pennies, I get pennies.

51:31.620 --> 51:33.520
I'm thinking dollars,
man.

51:34.857 --> 51:37.690
Ruth Brown's got
a tour booked in Georgia.

51:38.794 --> 51:40.022
She needs a band.

51:40.096 --> 51:41.120
I... I'll take it.

51:41.197 --> 51:43.927
I could write the charts
for her, I... I could do backup,

51:43.999 --> 51:46.058
and also be an openin' act.

51:49.004 --> 51:50.369
Okay.

51:50.473 --> 51:52.737
But you're going to be
financially responsible.

51:52.808 --> 51:54.742
You're gonna have
to make it work, Ray.

51:54.810 --> 51:57.335
Yeah, yeah, I'm gonna make it
do what it do, baby.

51:57.413 --> 51:58.778
Yeah.

52:10.926 --> 52:11.915
Ray!

52:12.161 --> 52:14.595
Miss Antwine,
it's been two weeks.

52:14.663 --> 52:16.392
It's been three.

52:22.071 --> 52:24.539
Now, where's the preacher at?
And the wife?

52:24.640 --> 52:26.733
They in Dallas till Monday.

52:26.809 --> 52:28.572
Well, hallelujah!

52:38.787 --> 52:40.186
Della Bea.

52:41.056 --> 52:42.853
Kind of like a honey bee,
right?

52:46.795 --> 52:48.456
Can I call you Bea?

52:49.465 --> 52:51.763
Yeah, I'd like that.

52:54.637 --> 52:58.471
There's only been two cats
that I ever really
trusted in my life.

53:00.075 --> 53:03.238
There's Jeff Brown,
he's going to be
my tour manager,

53:04.079 --> 53:06.411
Fathead Newman,
my tenor man

53:08.584 --> 53:10.051
and now you.

53:17.793 --> 53:19.158
But you gotta
do me a favor.

53:19.228 --> 53:21.321
Bea, you gotta
always tell me the truth.

53:21.397 --> 53:23.524
Oh, yeah. Just like
you did before.

53:24.400 --> 53:27.392
Don't feel sorry for me
just 'cause I'm blind.

53:28.504 --> 53:30.995
How could I pity
someone I admire?

53:36.011 --> 53:37.501
Can I play
something for you?

53:37.580 --> 53:39.172
Now?
Yeah.

53:39.248 --> 53:40.374
No, Ray.

53:40.449 --> 53:42.383
Yeah, right now.
Right now. I'm gonna...

53:42.451 --> 53:43.577
Ray!

53:47.456 --> 53:49.356
It's right there.
You got it.

53:49.458 --> 53:50.652
Okay.

53:50.726 --> 53:51.954
Yeah, yeah,
this will work.

53:53.128 --> 53:55.460
Now you go ahead
and play. I'm gonna
close these drapes.

53:55.531 --> 53:56.520
All right.

53:56.599 --> 53:58.123
I don't want no
neighbors looking in.

53:58.200 --> 53:59.633
# Well #

54:00.169 --> 54:01.796
# I got a woman #

54:02.771 --> 54:04.204
# way over town #

54:04.773 --> 54:06.297
# She's good to me #

54:07.343 --> 54:08.571
# Oh, yeah #

54:09.411 --> 54:10.901
# I got a woman #

54:11.780 --> 54:13.247
# Way over town #

54:13.315 --> 54:14.304
Ray.

54:14.383 --> 54:15.645
# She's good to me #

54:16.585 --> 54:17.950
# Oh, yeah #

54:18.053 --> 54:19.042
Ray!

54:19.121 --> 54:20.383
# She give me money #

54:20.456 --> 54:21.946
Ray. Ray, that's
sacrilegious.

54:22.024 --> 54:23.048
# When I'm in need ##

54:23.125 --> 54:24.319
What... what?

54:24.393 --> 54:26.088
It's a gospel song.

54:26.829 --> 54:28.888
I know what it is.
I wrote it.

54:29.531 --> 54:31.999
I mean, you told me
to find my own voice.

54:32.067 --> 54:33.659
Well, Bea, this is it.

54:33.736 --> 54:37.866
But it... it ain't... It ain't
right to be changing
gospel music into this.

54:37.940 --> 54:39.840
Into what? Is it...
Is it devil music?

54:39.908 --> 54:42.934
Evil music? Do you think...
Do you think I'm evil, Bea?

54:43.545 --> 54:45.775
Look, I've been
performing gospel

54:45.848 --> 54:48.043
and blues all my life.
It's who I am.

54:48.617 --> 54:52.144
And if I'm gonna
do my own thing,
I... I gotta be natural, right?

54:53.722 --> 54:56.316
I'm singing about
my feelings for you.

54:56.759 --> 54:58.420
About how I love you.

55:00.963 --> 55:03.227
What could be more
natural than that?

55:04.466 --> 55:05.728
Huh, Bea?

55:06.302 --> 55:07.633
Tell me.

55:08.704 --> 55:10.763
More natural
than me and you.

55:11.307 --> 55:12.296
Ray.

55:16.845 --> 55:18.710
# I got a woman #

55:19.381 --> 55:21.372
# Way over town #

55:23.052 --> 55:24.485
# good to me #

55:25.921 --> 55:27.115
# Oh, yeah ##

55:28.557 --> 55:30.991
So we bite the bullet,
we cancel the tour dates.

55:31.060 --> 55:32.925
But what the hell
are we gonna tell Ray?

55:32.995 --> 55:34.826
We just have
to tell him the truth:

55:34.897 --> 55:36.694
Ruth Brown's pregnant,
so there's no tour.

55:36.765 --> 55:38.562
What about LaVern Baker?

55:38.667 --> 55:40.658
Get LaVern Baker
to take the tour.

55:40.736 --> 55:42.931
She doesn't have a record.
There's nothing to promote.

55:43.005 --> 55:45.166
You and Jesse get up there,
write a couple of songs,

55:45.240 --> 55:46.639
let's get her in the studio.

55:46.709 --> 55:48.404
It's gonna take
a month to do that...

55:48.477 --> 55:50.445
What are we gonna do?
We got to do somethin'.

55:50.512 --> 55:52.173
Ray's got a whole
new band up there.

55:52.247 --> 55:54.579
How the hell did he put
together a band so fast?

55:54.650 --> 55:57.084
Boss! Boss,
they're here.

55:57.152 --> 55:59.950
Come on. Let's get together
so we can show 'em this.

56:00.022 --> 56:01.080
...break this to Ray.

56:01.156 --> 56:03.488
Oh, you're gonna let
me break it to Ray?

56:03.559 --> 56:04.526
Why me?

56:04.593 --> 56:05.958
Because Ruth Brown
was your idea.

56:06.028 --> 56:09.486
Ruth Brown is a good idea,
Ruth Brown was a good idea,
and still is a good idea.

56:09.565 --> 56:10.554
Shh!

56:10.632 --> 56:11.860
# That's good to me #

56:12.601 --> 56:14.125
# Oh, yeah #

56:14.870 --> 56:16.895
# I got a woman #

56:17.740 --> 56:19.469
# Way over town #

56:20.142 --> 56:21.632
# Good to me #

56:22.644 --> 56:24.168
# Whoa, yeah #

56:24.580 --> 56:26.514
# She give me money #

56:27.216 --> 56:29.411
# When I'm in need #

56:29.752 --> 56:31.743
# Yeah, she's the kind of #

56:32.388 --> 56:33.878
# friend indeed #

56:34.656 --> 56:35.953
# I got a woman #

56:36.058 --> 56:37.047
Ahmet.

56:37.292 --> 56:38.350
Yeah.

56:38.427 --> 56:40.292
We gotta get this on wax.

56:40.829 --> 56:41.921
Oh, yeah.

56:42.231 --> 56:43.220
# Oh, yeah #

56:43.399 --> 56:46.835
Hear that, New York?
The sound is huge!

56:46.902 --> 56:49.598
But there's only seven cats
on this record.

56:49.671 --> 56:52.231
This is the new
Ray Charles, baby,

56:52.307 --> 56:54.434
and there's nothing
out there like it!

56:54.510 --> 56:57.411
<i>And you heard it first
on The Moondog Show!</i>

56:59.047 --> 57:00.708
<i># Just for me #</i>

57:01.483 --> 57:02.950
<i># Oh, yeah #</i>

57:03.719 --> 57:05.186
<i># She give me money ##</i>

57:06.255 --> 57:08.917
The Shaw Agency's
the best booker
on the Chitlin' Circuit,

57:08.991 --> 57:10.288
that's my opinion.

57:10.359 --> 57:12.384
Milt Shaw, meet Ray Charles.

57:12.461 --> 57:14.292
Ray, It was
Milt's dad, Billy,

57:14.363 --> 57:16.957
who first drew my attention
to a certain blind pianist

57:17.032 --> 57:19.023
when he was
booking Lowell Fulson.

57:19.101 --> 57:21.535
Ray Charles.
We believe in your talent.

57:21.603 --> 57:24.197
We wanna be
in the Ray Charles business.

57:24.273 --> 57:26.707
We've already got you
booked on a 10-city tour

57:26.775 --> 57:28.265
with Roy Milton's
Solid Senders...

57:28.343 --> 57:29.537
Oh, Roy Milton,
I love him.

57:29.611 --> 57:32.512
...and Tangula
the Exotic Shake Dancer.

57:32.681 --> 57:35.241
She is gorgeous.

57:35.384 --> 57:36.681
Ray,
I gotta tell you,

57:36.752 --> 57:39.243
we think you're onto
something very big here.

57:39.321 --> 57:42.415
Nobody's ever combined
R&B and gospel before.

57:42.491 --> 57:43.890
<i>I've Got A Woman is a smash.</i>

57:43.959 --> 57:46.792
You better start thinking
about a follow-up, my friend.
Right now.

57:46.862 --> 57:49.023
You know, this sounds good.
I gotta run to Texas

57:49.097 --> 57:51.691
and take care
of some business,
and, I'll be right back.

57:51.767 --> 57:54.361
Well, make it fast. I'm ready
to sell, sell, sell.

57:54.436 --> 57:57.701
A- a-as long as you book
me in front of Tangula.

57:57.773 --> 57:59.536
Della, hold on!
Let me get my camera.

57:59.608 --> 58:00.939
Let me get one picture.

58:01.009 --> 58:03.170
Y'all, y'all,
stay right there! Ray!

58:04.146 --> 58:05.773
Della, let me
get one picture!

58:05.848 --> 58:07.873
Come on. One picture, Della!
Come on, now.

58:09.151 --> 58:10.311
Be careful, Ray.

58:10.385 --> 58:12.046
These are your last steps
of freedom, man.

58:12.120 --> 58:13.417
Don't open that door.

58:13.489 --> 58:16.322
Ray, you gotta carry her
over the threshold.

58:23.866 --> 58:26.232
To the right, Ray!
To the right, now!

58:29.371 --> 58:31.134
Ray, you need some help?

58:31.206 --> 58:33.037
You sure you know
what you're doing?

58:33.108 --> 58:35.303
<i># He knows a woman's place #</i>

58:35.377 --> 58:36.935
<i># Right there now,
in her home #</i>

58:37.012 --> 58:38.479
<i># I got a woman ##</i>

58:44.152 --> 58:45.141
Ray.

58:46.955 --> 58:47.944
Ray.

58:49.358 --> 58:51.019
Can I come in?

58:52.294 --> 58:53.852
H- H-Hold on.

58:53.996 --> 58:55.588
What's goin' on, Ray?

58:59.835 --> 59:01.496
Open this door.

59:02.704 --> 59:04.604
Why are you
locking doors
on me, Ray?

59:05.807 --> 59:07.001
You know
the place is small.

59:07.075 --> 59:08.474
We gotta have
a little privacy.

59:08.544 --> 59:10.978
Uh, what we need is
a little more room.

59:11.046 --> 59:14.311
You know, we're gonna
need some space
while we start a family.

59:15.584 --> 59:18.747
Well, Bea, you know
I'm gonna be on the road
for most of the year.

59:18.820 --> 59:19.809
Ray.

59:21.156 --> 59:24.182
I'm just thinking,
what if I'm not
a good father?

59:24.726 --> 59:26.284
My daddy
was never around.

59:26.361 --> 59:28.522
And he had
three different families.

59:30.499 --> 59:31.727
Well,

59:32.834 --> 59:35.997
you are gonna have one,
starting right now.

59:36.071 --> 59:37.060
Right now?

59:37.139 --> 59:38.128
Mmm-hmm.

59:39.007 --> 59:40.406
Well, what do you think?

59:41.610 --> 59:42.577
That's all is
what I know.

59:44.046 --> 59:45.411
<i># I know #</i>

59:45.647 --> 59:47.740
# Hallelujah,
I just love her so #

01:00:07.202 --> 01:00:09.602
# Now, if I call her
on the telephone #

01:00:10.372 --> 01:00:12.397
# And tell her
that I'm all alone #

01:00:13.308 --> 01:00:15.572
# By the time I count
from one to four #

01:00:16.244 --> 01:00:17.268
# I hear her #

01:00:17.646 --> 01:00:18.635
# on my door #

01:00:19.581 --> 01:00:21.572
Stop it!
Y'all done lost your minds!

01:00:21.650 --> 01:00:22.708
Stop all this stuff!

01:00:22.784 --> 01:00:23.842
You need to be saved!

01:00:23.919 --> 01:00:25.250
I can't take it
no more. Stop it!

01:00:25.320 --> 01:00:26.378
I can't take it!

01:00:26.455 --> 01:00:28.150
Hold on. Now,
wait a minute, man.

01:00:28.223 --> 01:00:29.588
Take your hands off me!

01:00:29.658 --> 01:00:31.353
This ain't right!

01:00:31.493 --> 01:00:33.893
Just let the people
hear the music.

01:00:34.196 --> 01:00:37.131
Y'all sitting here,
listenin' to this devil!

01:00:37.199 --> 01:00:40.362
You're just givin'
your money to Satan,
that's what you're doin'.

01:00:40.435 --> 01:00:42.403
<i>Hold on,
y- you got a problem?</i>

01:00:42.471 --> 01:00:44.063
Yeah, I got a problem!

01:00:44.139 --> 01:00:45.970
That's gospel
you're singin'!

01:00:46.041 --> 01:00:48.168
You're turning
God's music into sex.

01:00:48.243 --> 01:00:50.234
You're making
money off the Lord!

01:00:50.312 --> 01:00:53.145
Don't y'all smile at me!
All of y'all are in it, too!

01:00:53.215 --> 01:00:55.274
All of y'all are
going straight to hell!

01:00:55.350 --> 01:00:56.374
She's right.

01:00:58.086 --> 01:00:59.246
No, this here's wrong.

01:00:59.321 --> 01:01:00.515
The whole thing's wrong.

01:01:01.723 --> 01:01:03.520
It's okay. It's okay.
Let... let him go.

01:01:04.693 --> 01:01:06.490
You got a right to believe
in what you believe.

01:01:06.561 --> 01:01:08.722
You can go
to hell by yourself!

01:01:08.797 --> 01:01:10.321
Boss, you want
to cancel the show?

01:01:10.399 --> 01:01:11.764
Uh, no. I'm not gonna
cancel the show.

01:01:11.833 --> 01:01:13.391
Just find me
a bari player by tomorrow.

01:01:13.468 --> 01:01:15.834
I just want to ask
the folks right now:

01:01:15.904 --> 01:01:18.896
If all of y'all want me
to keep playing,
let me hear you say "Amen."

01:01:18.974 --> 01:01:20.965
Amen!

01:01:21.043 --> 01:01:22.840
And while you're at it,
find me a girl

01:01:22.911 --> 01:01:24.469
with church-training
that can sing

01:01:24.546 --> 01:01:25.706
but without
the church attitude.

01:01:25.781 --> 01:01:26.839
All right.

01:01:26.915 --> 01:01:29.179
Let's go, y'all.
Keep it going, here we go...

01:01:29.251 --> 01:01:30.411
Come on.

01:01:37.359 --> 01:01:39.384
<i># Let me tell you
'bout a girl I know #</i>

01:01:40.095 --> 01:01:42.620
<i># She is my baby
and she lives next door ##</i>

01:01:47.469 --> 01:01:48.902
Ray, you got your watch?

01:01:48.970 --> 01:01:49.994
Yeah.

01:01:50.072 --> 01:01:53.701
Good. All right, baby,
your blue shirts are on top,

01:01:53.775 --> 01:01:57.211
the pants in between,
and the white shirts are
on the bottom.

01:01:57.612 --> 01:02:00.274
Here's your glasses.
There you go.

01:02:01.950 --> 01:02:02.939
Bea.

01:02:03.418 --> 01:02:05.716
Why don't you come,
go on the road with us?

01:02:05.787 --> 01:02:07.880
Look, baby, what would
I do on the road?

01:02:07.956 --> 01:02:10.322
You'd do what I say
you do, that's what
you're gonna do.

01:02:11.493 --> 01:02:15.259
I've been trying
to get a female voice
in the band, anyway.

01:02:15.330 --> 01:02:18.163
Can't you just
picture me wobbling
around on that stage,

01:02:18.233 --> 01:02:19.461
big as a house?

01:02:19.534 --> 01:02:21.525
Well, I can't picture you,
you know that.

01:02:21.603 --> 01:02:23.093
But I know
what I can do.

01:02:24.773 --> 01:02:27.537
Come on, now.
Don't start nothing
you can't finish.

01:02:27.609 --> 01:02:29.042
Jeff is waiting.

01:02:30.512 --> 01:02:32.707
You know I can't go
on the road with you,

01:02:32.781 --> 01:02:34.271
not with your baby inside me.

01:02:34.349 --> 01:02:35.373
Mmm-hmm.

01:02:35.450 --> 01:02:37.418
I'm gonna get
your shaving kit.

01:02:38.420 --> 01:02:40.251
Uh, Bea,
I... I got it.

01:02:40.889 --> 01:02:42.516
Bea, hold... hold on.

01:02:46.928 --> 01:02:48.486
Bea, let me get it.

01:02:49.531 --> 01:02:52.091
How long you been
hiding this from me?

01:02:53.535 --> 01:02:54.524
Ray!

01:02:55.971 --> 01:02:57.302
I'm your wife!

01:02:57.405 --> 01:02:59.270
Bea, I... I was just so
excited to see you.

01:02:59.341 --> 01:03:01.639
I forgot to leave it
back there with the band,
that's all.

01:03:01.710 --> 01:03:03.041
Let me...
Let me get it.

01:03:03.111 --> 01:03:05.341
Oh, it's just
a little medicine,
that's all, baby.

01:03:05.413 --> 01:03:06.846
That ain't medicine
to nobody, Ray.

01:03:06.915 --> 01:03:08.280
Don't be lyin' to yourself.

01:03:08.350 --> 01:03:09.942
It ain't like I'm
dealing it, baby.

01:03:10.018 --> 01:03:11.508
I just use it
to get a little taste.

01:03:11.586 --> 01:03:13.349
You don't taste poison,
Ray. It kills you.

01:03:13.421 --> 01:03:14.445
Now, you got to stop.

01:03:14.523 --> 01:03:16.684
I ain't got to do
a goddamn thing!

01:03:18.260 --> 01:03:20.888
What about me?
What about your baby?

01:03:21.563 --> 01:03:22.552
Bea.

01:03:22.831 --> 01:03:25.026
It ain't like
I'm new to this.

01:03:25.534 --> 01:03:28.230
If I felt like
this was jeopardizing
my music, or you,

01:03:28.303 --> 01:03:29.702
or providing
for that baby,

01:03:29.771 --> 01:03:31.898
I would stop in a minute.
But I know it won't.

01:03:31.973 --> 01:03:34.498
How do you know that,
Ray? How do...
How do you know that?

01:03:34.576 --> 01:03:37.010
You know what?
You can talk till
you're blue in the face,

01:03:37.078 --> 01:03:38.773
it don't matter.
I'm not gonna stop.

01:03:38.847 --> 01:03:39.836
Then I'm comin'
with you.

01:03:39.915 --> 01:03:40.813
No, no.

01:03:40.882 --> 01:03:41.940
Well, Ray,
you just said...

01:03:42.017 --> 01:03:43.644
No. No.
You know what it is, Bea.

01:03:43.718 --> 01:03:45.618
I... I think
it's like you said.

01:03:46.054 --> 01:03:49.353
I don't think that
the road is a place
