Look at that
huge coconut tree!

01:32:48.161 --> 01:32:50.459
That ain't
no coconut tree, Della.
That's a palm tree.

01:32:50.530 --> 01:32:51.554
There's thousands
of them.

01:32:52.632 --> 01:32:53.621
Okay.

01:32:53.733 --> 01:32:55.963
Here's the keys
to your life,
a brand-new life.

01:32:58.672 --> 01:33:00.299
Oh, Ray.

01:33:03.443 --> 01:33:05.434
Ray, this is too much.

01:33:05.712 --> 01:33:07.703
Have you seen
the dining room?

01:33:10.850 --> 01:33:12.784
But, baby,
it's October.

01:33:12.886 --> 01:33:14.786
But you know what,
I wanted to
celebrate early,

01:33:14.854 --> 01:33:17.482
because the band
is gonna be playing
during the holidays.

01:33:19.659 --> 01:33:21.024
You are unbelievable.

01:33:21.094 --> 01:33:22.152
Look at your presents.

01:33:22.262 --> 01:33:24.059
Baby, look at what
Santa brought you.

01:33:24.130 --> 01:33:25.324
You must have been good.

01:33:25.398 --> 01:33:27.764
Go ahead!
Christmas is early,
baby!

01:33:27.834 --> 01:33:28.994
Go get it.

01:33:29.169 --> 01:33:30.295
What's he taken?
A guitar.

01:33:30.370 --> 01:33:32.065
A musician just
like your daddy.

01:33:32.138 --> 01:33:33.196
Can you play?

01:33:35.175 --> 01:33:36.107
Hello?

01:33:36.176 --> 01:33:37.666
What else you got?

01:33:37.811 --> 01:33:38.869
What's that?

01:33:38.945 --> 01:33:40.037
How'd you get this number?

01:33:41.147 --> 01:33:42.671
How do you think I got it?

01:33:42.816 --> 01:33:44.340
Put Ray on the phone.

01:33:46.019 --> 01:33:48.510
Ray, telephone.

01:33:48.855 --> 01:33:50.152
Deal with it, man.

01:33:50.223 --> 01:33:52.885
Ray, it's important.
Telephone.

01:33:53.860 --> 01:33:54.827
I-I'll be right back.

01:33:54.894 --> 01:33:56.122
All right.

01:33:56.863 --> 01:33:58.296
Who is it?

01:33:59.032 --> 01:34:00.693
It's Margie, man.

01:34:04.404 --> 01:34:07.396
Junior, come... come
and help your mama
change your brother's diaper.

01:34:07.507 --> 01:34:08.906
I don't want to go.

01:34:08.975 --> 01:34:10.499
I want to stay and
open my presents.

01:34:10.577 --> 01:34:12.169
All right, come on!
I don't want to go.

01:34:12.245 --> 01:34:14.076
I don't care.
Don't let me tell you twice.

01:34:14.147 --> 01:34:15.739
<i>Hello.
Hey, baby.</i>

01:34:16.149 --> 01:34:19.516
Surprise! I came to L.A.
to surprise you.

01:34:19.586 --> 01:34:21.144
Surprise me?
Are you out of your mind?

01:34:21.221 --> 01:34:22.586
I'm with my wife
and my kids.

01:34:22.656 --> 01:34:25.022
Well, on the road,
I'm Mrs. Ray Charles.

01:34:25.091 --> 01:34:26.217
That's on the road.

01:34:26.359 --> 01:34:29.851
Yeah, but, baby, come on,
I got everything
set up for us.

01:34:30.263 --> 01:34:32.094
Did you hear what
I just said to you, huh?

01:34:32.198 --> 01:34:34.860
Oh, wait a minute,
baby, look,
I got a bottle of Bols, and...

01:34:34.934 --> 01:34:37.903
Shut up. Shut up.
Listen, we record in
two weeks, okay?

01:34:37.971 --> 01:34:38.938
I'll see you then.

01:34:39.005 --> 01:34:40.973
<i>Wait a minute, Ray!
Bye.</i>

01:34:41.041 --> 01:34:42.303
Ray!

01:34:45.111 --> 01:34:49.104
<i># One of these days,
and it won't be long #</i>

01:34:51.918 --> 01:34:54.250
<i># You're gonna look for me #</i>

01:34:54.320 --> 01:34:57.153
<i># and I'll be gone #</i>

01:34:57.223 --> 01:34:58.747
<i># 'Cause I believe #</i>

01:34:58.825 --> 01:35:01.885
<i># I believe, yes #</i>

01:35:03.630 --> 01:35:05.598
<i># I say I believe right now #</i>

01:35:05.665 --> 01:35:07.895
<i># I believe #</i>

01:35:08.201 --> 01:35:10.101
# Yes I believe #

01:35:10.437 --> 01:35:14.897
# Well I believe
to my soul now #

01:35:16.209 --> 01:35:18.439
# You're tryin' to make
a fool of me #

01:35:19.012 --> 01:35:22.948
# I believe, yes I believe ##

01:35:23.016 --> 01:35:24.506
Hold on, wait, wait.

01:35:24.584 --> 01:35:26.882
Cut, cut, cut.
You know, y'all know
that sounds off.

01:35:26.953 --> 01:35:29.353
Ahem, you know what,
the three-part harmony is off.

01:35:29.489 --> 01:35:32.287
Let's start it
all over again, uh,
from the top with the band.

01:35:33.359 --> 01:35:36.954
<i># I believe it,
I believe it ##</i>

01:35:37.030 --> 01:35:39.191
Whoa, pardner!
Uh, what was that?

01:35:39.432 --> 01:35:42.128
<i>I knew you'd like that,
Ray. It's an eight-track.
We just got it.</i>

01:35:42.202 --> 01:35:44.033
<i>We can record
each part separately.</i>

01:35:44.104 --> 01:35:46.834
Whoa, Nellie! You know,
I can't wait to see that.

01:35:48.007 --> 01:35:49.565
What's so funny?

01:35:49.642 --> 01:35:51.075
Nothing, "pardner."

01:35:52.612 --> 01:35:54.011
Margie's drunk. Jeff?

01:35:55.782 --> 01:35:57.249
You should go home
and sleep it off.

01:35:57.317 --> 01:35:59.285
Margie, come on now,
let me take you home.

01:35:59.352 --> 01:36:01.445
No! I'll leave when I'm good
and goddamn ready!

01:36:01.521 --> 01:36:03.148
She's good and goddamn
ready right now.

01:36:03.223 --> 01:36:05.453
Why don't you make me
leave this, sucker!

01:36:05.525 --> 01:36:07.959
Teach you to treat me
like some piece of meat!

01:36:08.595 --> 01:36:09.994
I ain't shutting up!

01:36:10.063 --> 01:36:11.724
Should we get in there?
No.

01:36:11.798 --> 01:36:13.163
Get them all out, right now.

01:36:13.233 --> 01:36:14.495
You'll have to make me leave!

01:36:14.567 --> 01:36:17.400
You know what, Jeff?
Get all of them out of here.

01:36:17.537 --> 01:36:19.596
You're a cold-ass bastard!

01:36:19.672 --> 01:36:20.866
Let go of me, Jeff!

01:36:20.940 --> 01:36:22.771
You're a cold-ass bastard,
Ray!

01:36:22.842 --> 01:36:26.369
See, he wouldn't spit on me
if my ass was on fire!

01:36:26.446 --> 01:36:27.538
Damn right I wouldn't.

01:36:27.614 --> 01:36:29.673
Put me down, Jeff!
Put me down! Damn it!

01:36:30.016 --> 01:36:31.313
You dropped your shoe.

01:36:33.353 --> 01:36:35.753
All right, come on,
let's get back to work.

01:36:35.822 --> 01:36:37.619
Tom, this is
what I want you to do.

01:36:37.690 --> 01:36:40.181
We'll lay my vocals down
and finish the harmony parts.

01:36:40.260 --> 01:36:42.751
<i>Uh, how're we gonna do
the harmonies, Ray?</i>

01:36:42.829 --> 01:36:43.887
<i>You sent the girls home.</i>

01:36:43.963 --> 01:36:46.329
I know what I did
with the girls.
Let me take care of that.

01:36:46.399 --> 01:36:49.368
You just turn that
eight-track on, and I'll do
the girls' parts myself.

01:36:49.435 --> 01:36:52.336
And go out here
somewhere and find me
an "Oh, Johnny" girl.

01:36:52.705 --> 01:36:54.332
<i>Uh, one minute.</i>

01:36:55.341 --> 01:36:56.933
What the hell's
an "Oh, Johnny" girl?

01:36:57.076 --> 01:36:58.668
I think I've got an idea.

01:36:59.179 --> 01:37:02.945
<i># Last night
you were dreaming #</i>

01:37:03.016 --> 01:37:05.814
<i># and I heard you say #</i>

01:37:07.754 --> 01:37:09.551
<i># Oh, Johnny! #</i>

01:37:09.689 --> 01:37:12.988
<i># When you know
my name is Ray #</i>

01:37:13.059 --> 01:37:14.686
<i># That's why
I believe right now #</i>

01:37:14.761 --> 01:37:16.422
<i># I believe #</i>

01:37:17.263 --> 01:37:19.731
<i># Yes I believe #</i>

01:37:19.799 --> 01:37:21.460
<i># I say I believe right now #</i>

01:37:21.534 --> 01:37:23.934
<i># I believe #</i>

01:37:24.003 --> 01:37:27.131
<i># Yes I believe ##</i>

01:37:27.774 --> 01:37:29.765
<i>The sky's the limit, Ray.</i>

01:37:29.909 --> 01:37:31.934
<i>I got you
a $5,000-a-night raise.</i>

01:37:32.178 --> 01:37:34.043
They're gonna up you
to 15 per.

01:37:34.180 --> 01:37:35.613
Rehearsal in
10 minutes.

01:37:35.682 --> 01:37:37.445
Jeff, could you get
me some cigarettes?

01:37:38.084 --> 01:37:39.415
Okay, boss.

01:37:41.855 --> 01:37:43.288
15 per, huh?

01:37:43.356 --> 01:37:47.520
You know, Ray,
your contract with Atlantic
is expiring in four months.

01:37:47.861 --> 01:37:48.885
Yeah.

01:37:48.962 --> 01:37:50.896
Yeah, I've got
the contract with me.

01:37:51.030 --> 01:37:52.964
They're going to
double my royalties.

01:37:53.032 --> 01:37:54.966
Before we jump back
in that pond,

01:37:55.101 --> 01:37:57.296
I thought I'd find out
what else was out there.

01:37:57.370 --> 01:38:00.999
I had a very productive chat
with ABC-Paramount yesterday.

01:38:01.107 --> 01:38:03.041
ABC? Who told you
to do that, huh?

01:38:03.109 --> 01:38:06.101
And you know,
Atlantic is family,
just like the Shaw Agency.

01:38:06.179 --> 01:38:08.613
Ray, my job is to get you
the best deal possible.

01:38:09.282 --> 01:38:11.250
ABC is very interested.

01:38:11.317 --> 01:38:12.341
No.

01:38:14.988 --> 01:38:16.319
How interested?

01:38:17.190 --> 01:38:22.093
How about
a $50,000 advance
each year for three years?

01:38:22.161 --> 01:38:24.254
You produce
your own records.

01:38:24.631 --> 01:38:27.156
They'll deduct recording costs
and give you

01:38:27.533 --> 01:38:29.194
75 percent.

01:38:32.872 --> 01:38:35.670
Ahmet and Jerry are
flying in tonight,

01:38:36.009 --> 01:38:39.570
so will you put them off
until I can talk
things out with ABC?

01:38:41.681 --> 01:38:44.172
Well, my mama said,
ain't nothing wrong
with talking.

01:38:45.285 --> 01:38:46.309
Hey, enough of
the formalities.

01:38:46.386 --> 01:38:48.320
Come on, let's go back
into the office, Ray.

01:38:48.388 --> 01:38:49.446
I hope I can call you Ray.

01:38:49.522 --> 01:38:50.989
I want you to be
comfortable here.

01:38:51.057 --> 01:38:54.117
Because I'll tell you
something, everything is
gonna be better at ABC.

01:38:54.193 --> 01:38:56.093
Moving from an indie label
to a major

01:38:56.162 --> 01:38:57.789
means you can sell
a lot more records,

01:38:57.864 --> 01:39:01.163
as well as attract
much larger crowds,
both white and Negro.

01:39:01.234 --> 01:39:04.829
Yeah, but Mr. Clark,
you know, I've been
at Atlantic for so long,

01:39:05.338 --> 01:39:09.638
I just want to give
those guys a chance, you know,
to at least match the offer.

01:39:09.709 --> 01:39:11.973
Mm-hmm.
Oh, certainly, certainly.

01:39:12.078 --> 01:39:13.568
But, uh, I doubt
they'll be able to.

01:39:13.646 --> 01:39:15.637
We're giving you
a state-of-the-art deal here.

01:39:15.715 --> 01:39:19.082
Well, you know, since I'm
producing my own records,
I was wondering if I could

01:39:19.152 --> 01:39:20.983
uh, own my masters, too.

01:39:28.528 --> 01:39:29.552
Well,

01:39:29.629 --> 01:39:31.859
Ray, we've... we've never
done that before.

01:39:31.931 --> 01:39:33.956
No record company has.

01:39:34.100 --> 01:39:38.799
Well, I think I'm going to
have to have it that way for
me to leave Atlantic Records.

01:39:47.647 --> 01:39:49.979
Ahmet believes
we're family here at Atlantic.

01:39:50.049 --> 01:39:52.108
I believe we're family
here at Atlantic.

01:39:52.185 --> 01:39:54.016
Obviously, you don't!

01:39:54.487 --> 01:39:56.045
Ahmet wouldn't believe it.

01:39:56.122 --> 01:39:57.680
You know what he said, Ray?

01:39:57.757 --> 01:39:59.725
He said you would never
turn your back on us.

01:39:59.792 --> 01:40:01.919
Never for a schlockmeister
like Sam Clark!

01:40:03.096 --> 01:40:05.155
That's rich.
Sam Clark's a corporate slug,

01:40:05.231 --> 01:40:08.428
who wouldn't know
the difference between
Earl Hines and Art Tatum!

01:40:14.741 --> 01:40:16.800
We let you grow here, Ray.

01:40:17.110 --> 01:40:20.773
And nobody's taking
credit for your talent,
but we nourished it.

01:40:21.247 --> 01:40:23.238
We let you do your thing.

01:40:24.817 --> 01:40:27.012
God damn it!
We deserve better than this.

01:40:27.086 --> 01:40:29.145
You know what,
don't think that
I don't appreciate

01:40:29.222 --> 01:40:31.019
everything you guys
have done here, Jerry.

01:40:31.090 --> 01:40:33.718
Ahmet, I'm very
proud of the work that
we've done here together.

01:40:33.793 --> 01:40:37.024
But, Atlantic has done
pretty good money-wise
on my records, haven't they?

01:40:37.096 --> 01:40:38.529
Yes, we've done
very well, Ray.

01:40:38.598 --> 01:40:41.829
You... you were the ones that
taught me that making a record
is business,

01:40:41.901 --> 01:40:44.267
and find the best
business deal you can.

01:40:44.337 --> 01:40:47.602
Now, 75 cents of every dollar,
and owning my own masters

01:40:47.673 --> 01:40:49.800
is a pretty damn
good deal.

01:40:50.343 --> 01:40:51.970
Can you match it?

01:40:52.945 --> 01:40:57.041
Ray, we would love to
match it, but we just can't.

01:40:58.384 --> 01:41:01.217
That's a better deal
than Sinatra gets.

01:41:04.123 --> 01:41:05.590
I'm very proud of you.

01:41:08.094 --> 01:41:11.689
Looks like those boys
are going to get
a taste of country dumb.

01:41:11.764 --> 01:41:12.924
Yeah.

01:41:15.868 --> 01:41:17.199
He'll be all right, man.

01:41:18.371 --> 01:41:20.271
You guys
always do find the best.

01:41:37.523 --> 01:41:39.013
# Georgia #

01:41:41.394 --> 01:41:43.487
# Georgia #

01:41:45.264 --> 01:41:48.097
# The whole day through #

01:41:48.267 --> 01:41:51.065
# The whole day through #

01:41:51.137 --> 01:41:53.264
# Just an old sweet song #

01:41:56.109 --> 01:41:59.567
# Keeps Georgia on my mind #

01:41:59.645 --> 01:42:04.275
# Georgia on my mind #

01:42:05.418 --> 01:42:07.716
# I said Georgia #

01:42:11.324 --> 01:42:13.656
# Georgia #

01:42:13.726 --> 01:42:15.523
Listen to that crap.

01:42:16.762 --> 01:42:20.095
Thought you said that
ABC wasn't going to
force nothing on him.

01:42:20.333 --> 01:42:21.800
They didn't.

01:42:22.468 --> 01:42:24.163
It was Ray's idea.

01:42:26.272 --> 01:42:27.330
Something new.

01:42:27.406 --> 01:42:29.966
What are we then, Jeff?
Something old?

01:42:30.042 --> 01:42:33.705
Yeah, what about us?
We got to eat, too.

01:42:37.817 --> 01:42:42.754
# Other arms should
reach out to me #

01:42:45.191 --> 01:42:50.128
# Other eyes smile tenderly #

01:42:52.365 --> 01:42:57.325
# Still in the peaceful dreams
I see #

01:42:58.037 --> 01:43:02.736
# The road leads back
to you ##

01:43:10.783 --> 01:43:11.807
<i>It's a hit record.</i>

01:43:11.884 --> 01:43:13.442
<i>What the hell
is wrong with that?</i>

01:43:13.519 --> 01:43:16.079
Critics say you've gone
middle-of-the-road.

01:43:16.155 --> 01:43:19.249
<i>The orchestra, the choir,
The Perry Como Show, man?</i>

01:43:19.325 --> 01:43:22.852
If I feel the music,
that means it's real.

01:43:22.929 --> 01:43:25.591
No, it ain't.
Ray Charles is a sellout.

01:43:25.665 --> 01:43:28.657
The blind Liberace,
leaving those Rocking
Chair roots behind.

01:43:28.734 --> 01:43:29.723
Quincy Jones.

01:43:29.802 --> 01:43:31.667
Can we get a picture
of these two guys?

01:43:31.737 --> 01:43:33.602
Six-nine!
Hey, boy.

01:43:33.673 --> 01:43:36.107
Look, here, uh,
this interview is over.

01:43:36.175 --> 01:43:38.040
I'd love to
get you two together, man.

01:43:38.110 --> 01:43:39.509
S- some other time.

01:43:39.845 --> 01:43:42.473
Look at you.
How's it going, man?
You look good.

01:43:42.548 --> 01:43:44.607
Let me look at you.
You look good, too.

01:43:44.684 --> 01:43:46.345
You hear what they're
saying about me?

01:43:46.419 --> 01:43:49.513
I just said that I... I
can't do it no more.
I've gone middle-of-the-road.

01:43:49.589 --> 01:43:51.022
So crank out
another hit.

01:43:51.090 --> 01:43:52.216
Let me tell you something,

01:43:52.291 --> 01:43:54.725
it ain't easy
to keep on being greezy, kid.

01:43:55.194 --> 01:43:56.627
Where you blow in from?

01:43:57.830 --> 01:43:58.888
Paris.

01:43:58.965 --> 01:44:00.091
<i>Bonjour.</i>

01:44:00.166 --> 01:44:02.361
Yeah, man.
France is where it's at.

01:44:02.535 --> 01:44:04.628
Yeah, man. And all that stuff
you've been playing,

01:44:04.704 --> 01:44:07.104
man, it's just...
it really feels out of sight.

01:44:07.173 --> 01:44:09.664
You know, we gotta
record something together.

01:44:09.742 --> 01:44:11.505
I mean, people will
really dig it.

01:44:11.577 --> 01:44:13.442
So, where you going
after the Festival?

01:44:13.512 --> 01:44:17.312
Oh, I... I go to D.C., Richmond,
uh, Virginia, Georgia.

01:44:17.383 --> 01:44:20.250
You know what, once you
get the record out there,
you gotta sell it.

01:44:20.319 --> 01:44:21.752
The South, man?

01:44:22.955 --> 01:44:24.252
I'm not doing that no more.

01:44:24.323 --> 01:44:27.156
Hey, come on, kid,
that's where
the money is, baby.

01:44:27.226 --> 01:44:29.751
You know, When I left Seattle
with Hamp,

01:44:29.829 --> 01:44:31.057
we went down there, man.

01:44:31.130 --> 01:44:33.724
And it felt like
I walked into a prison cell.

01:44:33.799 --> 01:44:37.428
You know, a black man
is a "boy"
in Mississippi, Ray.

01:44:37.503 --> 01:44:39.437
Even if he's 80 years old.

01:44:42.675 --> 01:44:45.109
I'm never playing
to Jim Crow again. Ever.

01:44:45.177 --> 01:44:47.008
If that's what you feel,
baby.

01:44:47.079 --> 01:44:50.742
I'm serious, Ray.
Man, we gotta do something.

01:44:52.451 --> 01:44:54.351
Well, you know,
what... what the hell, man.

01:44:54.420 --> 01:44:57.787
You're just going
to leave a lot more money
on the table for me.

01:44:58.324 --> 01:44:59.985
You're welcome to it,
man.

01:45:15.107 --> 01:45:16.665
You ready to work?

01:45:16.742 --> 01:45:18.039
Work on what?

01:45:19.245 --> 01:45:21.110
Get over here, you gotta
help me with this.

01:45:21.180 --> 01:45:22.613
Percy just sent me
some new music.

01:45:36.662 --> 01:45:38.926
You know what
they're saying about me?

01:45:38.998 --> 01:45:41.432
Said I've lost something,
said I've gone
middle-of-the-road.

01:45:41.500 --> 01:45:43.764
They may as well say
the same thing about you.

01:45:43.836 --> 01:45:45.167
You were the soul
of this band.

01:45:45.237 --> 01:45:47.671
