01:58:00.138 --> 01:58:01.127
Hello?

01:58:02.607 --> 01:58:05.872
Don't jive me, Milt.
Don't jive me, man!

01:58:05.944 --> 01:58:07.070
Really?

01:58:07.412 --> 01:58:11.007
Ah, good, good, good.
Tell... tell Sam
I said thank you.

01:58:11.083 --> 01:58:13.074
All right.
All right, then.

01:58:14.619 --> 01:58:15.677
Oh, yeah!

01:58:15.754 --> 01:58:18.450
What, Ray?
What? Come on, now.

01:58:18.523 --> 01:58:20.354
Ray, tell me what happened.

01:58:20.425 --> 01:58:22.620
ABC got the case dropped.

01:58:22.694 --> 01:58:24.491
The police
didn't have a warrant.

01:58:24.563 --> 01:58:25.723
They bought them off.

01:58:25.797 --> 01:58:27.765
Damn it, Bea, do you
want me to go to prison?

01:58:27.833 --> 01:58:30.301
No. Ray, I want you
to stop lying to yourself,

01:58:30.368 --> 01:58:32.461
and they are making that
completely impossible.

01:58:32.537 --> 01:58:34.061
You know what,
you don't understand.

01:58:34.139 --> 01:58:35.834
Then make me understand,
Ray!

01:58:35.907 --> 01:58:39.274
Baby, when I walk out
that door, I walk out alone
in the dark!

01:58:39.344 --> 01:58:40.743
I'm trying to
do something

01:58:40.812 --> 01:58:43.508
that ain't nobody ever done
in music and business.

01:58:43.582 --> 01:58:46.244
But I can't do it
if I'm alone
everywhere I go.

01:58:46.852 --> 01:58:49.184
I don't want to
be alone here, Bea.

01:58:49.254 --> 01:58:51.017
Not in my own home.

01:58:54.659 --> 01:58:57.321
Look, Bea,
if you don't understand me,

01:58:58.196 --> 01:58:59.720
then who will?

01:59:06.271 --> 01:59:07.863
I don't know, Ray.

01:59:11.476 --> 01:59:13.808
David? I'm coming!

01:59:14.913 --> 01:59:16.380
Mama's coming!

01:59:20.185 --> 01:59:24.121
Ray, we pull you
out of the fire,
and you want country music?

01:59:24.189 --> 01:59:27.283
Look here, I've been singing
country music all my life.

01:59:27.359 --> 01:59:29.850
As a matter of fact,
I used to play with
the Florida Playboys.

01:59:29.928 --> 01:59:31.418
We made a big
investment in you

01:59:31.496 --> 01:59:32.963
and it's paying off
handsomely.

01:59:33.031 --> 01:59:34.726
For both of us,
I might add.

01:59:34.799 --> 01:59:36.357
We don't want to
lose your fan base.

01:59:36.434 --> 01:59:38.493
Yeah, you know,
you got a point there,

01:59:38.570 --> 01:59:42.028
but I actually think that
we have more to gain
than we do to lose.

01:59:42.974 --> 01:59:45.636
Ray, it's a bad idea.

01:59:47.679 --> 01:59:50.113
When I came to ABC, you guys
put in the contract

01:59:50.182 --> 01:59:52.241
that I can choose
my own music.

01:59:53.118 --> 01:59:54.847
You want to read
that paragraph?

01:59:59.057 --> 02:00:00.786
It's on page three.

02:00:02.127 --> 02:00:03.685
I don't need to see it.

02:00:13.071 --> 02:00:15.301
Good evening, Saint Louis.

02:00:15.373 --> 02:00:17.739
It's time
for the main attraction.

02:00:17.809 --> 02:00:21.370
The innovator of soul.
The genius himself.

02:00:21.713 --> 02:00:23.510
Ray Charles!

02:00:42.934 --> 02:00:44.128
Go on, go on, Ray!

02:00:49.307 --> 02:00:50.535
<i>Thank you so much.</i>

02:00:50.609 --> 02:00:53.772
<i>You know what,
I know that a lot of y'all
don't know that</i>

02:00:53.845 --> 02:00:57.008
<i>I... I was brought up
in the South.</i>

02:00:57.082 --> 02:01:00.210
<i>You know, every time
you turn on the radio there
in the South,</i>

02:01:00.285 --> 02:01:01.650
<i>you hear the Grand Ole Opry.</i>

02:01:01.720 --> 02:01:04.848
<i>That's what I grew up singing,
so I hope you don't mind,</i>

02:01:05.490 --> 02:01:08.982
<i>I... I want to sing something
to give you a taste
of my country roots.</i>

02:01:10.228 --> 02:01:11.525
<i>Unchain My Heart!</i>

02:01:11.730 --> 02:01:13.288
<i>Georgia on My Mind, Ray!</i>

02:01:15.600 --> 02:01:17.830
# I can't stop loving you #

02:01:18.470 --> 02:01:21.496
Turn 'em, the lights up top
and on the mezzanine,

02:01:21.906 --> 02:01:25.239
let's take everything down
and hit Ray
with a follow spot.

02:01:25.310 --> 02:01:26.800
We're doing it,
on it on my count.

02:01:27.145 --> 02:01:29.136
# To live in memory #

02:01:30.048 --> 02:01:32.209
IN 5, 4...

02:01:32.684 --> 02:01:35.881
# of the lonesome times #

02:01:36.988 --> 02:01:40.048
# Yeah #

02:01:40.125 --> 02:01:44.653
# I can't stop wanting you #

02:01:46.731 --> 02:01:50.599
# It's useless to say #

02:01:53.772 --> 02:01:57.503
# So I'll just live my life #

02:01:57.575 --> 02:01:59.873
# I'll live my life #

02:02:00.345 --> 02:02:03.678
# in dreams of yesterday #

02:02:07.319 --> 02:02:11.187
# Those happy hours #

02:02:11.256 --> 02:02:14.817
# Those happy hours #

02:02:15.093 --> 02:02:18.551
# that we once knew ##

02:02:19.898 --> 02:02:21.058
Cab's here.

02:02:21.132 --> 02:02:22.190
Okay.

02:02:22.267 --> 02:02:26.670
Dad, if you can't see,
how can you choose
the right color socks?

02:02:26.738 --> 02:02:28.672
I'm... I'm gonna show you,
all right?

02:02:28.740 --> 02:02:30.002
Let me show you something.

02:02:30.075 --> 02:02:31.940
See? Right here?

02:02:32.344 --> 02:02:35.336
The two, right there,
I got it sewn in thick,
so I can feel it.

02:02:35.480 --> 02:02:37.141
So, it means two is brown.

02:02:37.215 --> 02:02:39.547
One is black. Three is blue.

02:02:39.617 --> 02:02:41.380
And... and... and where's four?

02:02:41.486 --> 02:02:42.578
Nowhere.

02:02:42.654 --> 02:02:45.088
Four ain't nowhere.
There ain't no four.
You're right.

02:02:47.392 --> 02:02:50.384
# Heals a broken heart #

02:02:50.495 --> 02:02:53.430
# But time has stood still #

02:02:53.498 --> 02:02:56.194
# Time has stood still #

02:02:56.267 --> 02:02:59.634
# Since we've been apart #

02:02:59.704 --> 02:03:02.537
# Since we've been apart ##

02:03:20.692 --> 02:03:22.284
Still working on the balcony.

02:03:22.360 --> 02:03:24.123
Okay, guys, we got
10 minutes to load out!

02:03:24.195 --> 02:03:25.719
Change back at the hotel.

02:03:25.797 --> 02:03:27.856
They bought that
country jive hook,
line and sinker.

02:03:27.932 --> 02:03:29.126
Ray, man,
you're amazing.

02:03:29.200 --> 02:03:32.328
I'm gonna tell you something.
Country music.
You know why they like it?

02:03:32.404 --> 02:03:34.531
The stories, man.
They got great stories.

02:03:34.606 --> 02:03:35.664
Hey, Joe.

02:03:35.740 --> 02:03:39.107
Ray, I want to introduce you
to Joe Adams.
Hal Ziegler hired Joe

02:03:39.177 --> 02:03:41.543
as the announcer
for the rest of the tour.

02:03:41.613 --> 02:03:44.138
I know you,
Mayor of Melody.

02:03:44.215 --> 02:03:46.683
I used to listen to your
radio show in L.A.
In the '50s.

02:03:46.751 --> 02:03:49.311
We've both come
a ways since then.

02:03:49.387 --> 02:03:52.015
What was that counting
you were doing back there?

02:03:52.123 --> 02:03:54.683
I was cueing down the lights.
That shuts up the audience

02:03:54.759 --> 02:03:57.387
so you can sing your ballad
instead of
having to scream it.

02:03:57.462 --> 02:03:59.760
Hey, well, I'll be damned.
Who told you to do that?

02:03:59.831 --> 02:04:01.560
No one.
It just needed to be done.

02:04:01.633 --> 02:04:03.498
See, that's what
I'm talking about.

02:04:03.568 --> 02:04:06.469
I like to hear a person say
"It needed to be done"

02:04:06.538 --> 02:04:09.268
as opposed to
a person saying,
"It ain't my job."

02:04:09.741 --> 02:04:11.675
You know,
tell me about Central Avenue.

02:04:12.177 --> 02:04:13.041
I know you know
Jack Lauderdale.

02:04:14.212 --> 02:04:15.645
Hello, New York!

02:04:15.713 --> 02:04:17.044
Hello, Boston!

02:04:17.315 --> 02:04:18.646
Hello, Saint Louis!

02:04:18.716 --> 02:04:20.479
Good evening, San Francisco!

02:04:22.287 --> 02:04:24.050
<i># Bye bye love #</i>

02:04:25.023 --> 02:04:26.923
<i># Bye bye happiness #</i>

02:04:27.926 --> 02:04:29.553
Ray, I got
some good news for you.

02:04:29.627 --> 02:04:31.219
<i>We got the cover of Cash Box.</i>

02:04:31.296 --> 02:04:34.527
"The nation's hottest album:
Modern Sounds of
Country & Western."

02:04:34.599 --> 02:04:35.657
You are hotter
than hell.

02:04:35.733 --> 02:04:36.722
That's what they say.

02:04:36.801 --> 02:04:39.201
I've been watchin',
your albums are
going through the roof,

02:04:39.270 --> 02:04:40.999
your concerts are
always selling out.

02:04:41.072 --> 02:04:42.630
You'll need shelters
for your money.

02:04:42.707 --> 02:04:44.231
You're in a
new tax bracket.

02:04:44.309 --> 02:04:47.142
Keep your drawers on, Fathead!
I got the instruments!

02:04:47.212 --> 02:04:49.680
<i>Jeff, Joe was in
the film Carmen Jones.</i>

02:04:49.747 --> 02:04:51.271
Who was
the director again?

02:04:51.349 --> 02:04:52.407
Otto Preminger.

02:04:52.484 --> 02:04:55.578
He was also on Broadway
with Lena Horne.

02:04:55.720 --> 02:04:58.154
She was the star.
I was supporting.

02:04:58.323 --> 02:04:59.881
Is that a fact?

02:05:00.058 --> 02:05:03.289
<i>Prepare for an extraordinary
evening of music.</i>

02:05:03.361 --> 02:05:05.329
Perhaps the most innovative,
unique

02:05:05.396 --> 02:05:07.296
and energetic
musical voice today.

02:05:07.365 --> 02:05:08.662
Please welcome
to the stage...

02:05:08.733 --> 02:05:09.995
It is my distinct pleasure...

02:05:10.068 --> 02:05:12.366
Please give
your warmest welcome,
the one-of-a-kind...

02:05:12.437 --> 02:05:13.870
I present Mr. Ray...

02:05:13.938 --> 02:05:15.872
Ray... Ray Charles!

02:05:17.675 --> 02:05:19.438
# Bye bye love #

02:05:20.778 --> 02:05:22.678
# Bye bye sweet caress #

02:05:23.414 --> 02:05:25.211
# Hello emptiness #

02:05:25.316 --> 02:05:27.147
# I think I'm gonna die #

02:05:30.555 --> 02:05:32.216
<i># Bye bye love #</i>

02:05:38.196 --> 02:05:39.629
<i># I think I'm gonna die #</i>

02:05:43.234 --> 02:05:44.861
<i># I think I'm gonna die #</i>

02:05:45.069 --> 02:05:46.502
...Ray Charles!

02:05:48.273 --> 02:05:49.934
<i># I think I'm gonna die #</i>

02:05:50.975 --> 02:05:52.636
<i># I think I'm gonna die ##</i>

02:05:53.444 --> 02:05:55.639
Bea, there's a park right
at the end of the street.

02:05:55.713 --> 02:05:57.977
You can see the whole L.A.
basin from there.

02:05:58.049 --> 02:06:00.210
Not even Beverly Hills
has views like that.

02:06:00.285 --> 02:06:02.981
How does it look, Bea, huh?
You like it, don't you?

02:06:03.054 --> 02:06:04.578
I don't know.
I haven't seen it.

02:06:04.656 --> 02:06:06.089
You got to like it.

02:06:06.157 --> 02:06:07.146
Voilà.

02:06:07.225 --> 02:06:10.558
This foyer is designed
to impress anybody
who walks through the door.

02:06:10.628 --> 02:06:13.654
<i>It has a big
winding staircase,
just like Gone With the Wind.</i>

02:06:13.731 --> 02:06:16.894
We should get
our portraits painted,
like Rhett and Scarlett.

02:06:17.135 --> 02:06:18.625
Bea, bring him in here.

02:06:18.703 --> 02:06:21.103
Ray, wait till you hear
what's waiting
in the living room.

02:06:21.172 --> 02:06:22.161
What is it?

02:06:22.273 --> 02:06:26.107
I had them build you
a solid marble fireplace,
two stories high.

02:06:26.210 --> 02:06:28.371
Hot damn!
How do you like it, Bea?

02:06:28.446 --> 02:06:29.538
It's awful big.

02:06:29.614 --> 02:06:31.206
It sure is:
8,500 square feet.

02:06:31.282 --> 02:06:33.079
Biggest house in
the neighborhood.

02:06:33.151 --> 02:06:34.914
So, does this meet
with your approval?

02:06:34.986 --> 02:06:36.476
Man, this is a palace.

02:06:36.554 --> 02:06:39.045
You think this is big?
Wait until tomorrow
when you see

02:06:39.123 --> 02:06:41.421
30,000 square feet
of RPM Incorporated.

02:06:41.492 --> 02:06:43.255
Yeah, headquarters!

02:06:43.328 --> 02:06:45.694
This is it, Ray. Your
brand-new recording studio.

02:06:45.763 --> 02:06:47.390
Did you get
everything I asked for?

02:06:47.465 --> 02:06:48.727
Totally state-of-the-art.

02:06:48.800 --> 02:06:52.759
Tom Dowd built
an eight-track mixing console,
two recorders, the works.

02:06:52.837 --> 02:06:55.237
Now, this room is bigger
than most people's houses.

02:06:55.306 --> 02:06:57.740
Got your own private bathroom
to your left.

02:06:57.809 --> 02:07:00.073
Right behind you
is my adjoining office.

02:07:00.144 --> 02:07:02.510
And step over
to your private bar
to your left.

02:07:02.580 --> 02:07:04.480
Got a bottle of Bols
right in the center.

02:07:04.549 --> 02:07:05.948
You know me pretty good.

02:07:06.017 --> 02:07:08.417
If you run out, shout,
I'm right next door.

02:07:08.753 --> 02:07:10.084
This is nice, right here.

02:07:10.154 --> 02:07:11.553
It's the house
that Ray built.

02:07:11.623 --> 02:07:12.681
Yes, it is.

02:07:12.957 --> 02:07:14.652
<i># Born to lose #</i>

02:07:16.327 --> 02:07:20.024
<i># I've lived my life
in vain ##</i>

02:07:24.736 --> 02:07:26.533
Ray Junior, slow down!

02:07:26.604 --> 02:07:28.469
This ain't no
baseball diamond!

02:07:30.942 --> 02:07:32.603
Charles residence.

02:07:33.277 --> 02:07:34.904
Mr. Charles?

02:07:35.113 --> 02:07:37.604
Hey, girl,
Bring that boy over here!

02:07:37.682 --> 02:07:39.843
I got a hot dog
with his name on it!
Come on, now.

02:07:39.917 --> 02:07:41.077
Hello.

02:07:41.552 --> 02:07:43.679
Uh, yes,
I know who you are.

02:07:44.989 --> 02:07:47.150
What? Oh, God, no.

02:07:47.725 --> 02:07:48.657
Ray.

02:07:48.726 --> 02:07:52.218
Yes, I'll get on a plane
and I'll be there
as soon as I can.

02:07:52.296 --> 02:07:53.627
What happened?

02:07:55.767 --> 02:07:57.098
Margie's dead.

02:07:57.468 --> 02:07:59.129
Oh, God! H-How?

02:08:00.905 --> 02:08:02.395
She overdosed.

02:08:05.777 --> 02:08:07.574
I didn't start her, Bea.

02:08:08.713 --> 02:08:10.203
I didn't let her
do dope around me.

02:08:10.281 --> 02:08:12.249
I... I just wouldn't
let that happen.

02:08:12.316 --> 02:08:15.581
Yes, I'm sure, Ray.
I'm sure you set
a fine example.

02:08:19.724 --> 02:08:21.487
What about her baby?

02:08:25.963 --> 02:08:27.225
You knew?

02:08:27.965 --> 02:08:29.990
His name is Charles Wayne.

02:08:30.368 --> 02:08:34.202
He was born October 1,
in New York City.
He's 3 years old.

02:08:35.173 --> 02:08:36.663
The baby's fine.

02:08:37.575 --> 02:08:39.372
He's at her sister's.

02:08:41.145 --> 02:08:43.113
All right.
I'll start sending them
some money.

02:08:43.181 --> 02:08:46.275
You don't have to.
I send them
money every month.

02:09:11.142 --> 02:09:12.734
In five minutes,
Mr. Charles will be here,

02:09:12.810 --> 02:09:14.277
and he'll be ready to go.

02:09:14.345 --> 02:09:15.903
Now the charts
Jeff is handing out

02:09:15.980 --> 02:09:18.778
should be turned in
at the conclusion of...

02:09:19.217 --> 02:09:21.447
You're late,
that's a $50 fine.

02:09:22.019 --> 02:09:23.452
I ain't late.

02:09:23.521 --> 02:09:25.614
I give them
a 10-minute grace period, Joe.

02:09:25.690 --> 02:09:28.989
2:05. He's late.
He'll be charged $50.

02:09:29.060 --> 02:09:31.551
What? You know what?
Where's Ray?

02:09:31.629 --> 02:09:33.995
You don't have to talk to Ray,
you're talking to me.

02:09:34.065 --> 02:09:38.263
I'll talk to whoever
I damn well please,
and it sure as hell ain't you.

02:09:38.336 --> 02:09:39.667
Jive jerk.

02:09:44.408 --> 02:09:45.568
Hey, Ray,

02:09:45.643 --> 02:09:49.773
this fool Joe Adams
is trying to fine me
for being late.

02:09:50.081 --> 02:09:51.548
What time did you get here?

02:09:51.616 --> 02:09:55.609
What? Just now.
The band's still setting up.

02:09:56.220 --> 02:09:57.847
Jeff don't...
Look, I'm not Jeff.

02:09:57.922 --> 02:09:59.685
That's a fact, Jack!

02:10:00.858 --> 02:10:03.520
Ray, you said
the band was my thing.

02:10:03.594 --> 02:10:05.061
It is.

02:10:05.129 --> 02:10:07.791
Then, Fathead,
you go on back to rehearsal.

02:10:08.833 --> 02:10:10.198
Ray.

02:10:10.635 --> 02:10:13.069
Ray, you know how it is,
you've been there.

02:10:13.604 --> 02:10:15.936
Fathead, go on now.
Let me handle this.

02:10:16.007 --> 02:10:17.736
Fathead, go on now.

02:10:21.179 --> 02:10:23.272
You want to tell me
what the hell
is going on, Ray?

02:10:23.347 --> 02:10:25.372
I'm not doing anything
I haven't been asked to.

02:10:25.449 --> 02:10:27.007
Ray's running a business.

02:10:27.084 --> 02:10:30.110
He shouldn't
have to waste time
hearing why people were late.

02:10:30.188 --> 02:10:31.985
I'm not talking
to you, Joe.

02:10:32.056 --> 02:10:33.785
I'm talking to Ray.

02:10:38.763 --> 02:10:41.698
Ray, now I know you think
I'm soft on the band,

02:10:41.766 --> 02:10:44.132
but those cats would do
whatever I ask.

02:10:44.202 --> 02:10:46.864
But If you come in here
with this, uh,
"running a business" crap,

02:10:46.938 --> 02:10:49.168
you're gonna lose
some good people.
I'm telling you, Ray.

02:10:49.240 --> 02:10:51.640
There are musicians
waiting in line
to play with Ray Charles.

02:10:51.709 --> 02:10:54.542
Not for long,
once they get a taste of you.

02:10:55.213 --> 02:10:57.443
Ray, you're the leader, man.
Be one! Come on, now.

02:10:57.515 --> 02:10:59.506
You now what Jeff, I mean
things have changed.

02:10:59.584 --> 02:11:02.644
It ain't like the days
when it was seven of us
on the Chitlin' Circuit.

02:11:02.720 --> 02:11:06.178
I mean, if you weren't busy
building a bowling alley,
you'd seen that.

02:11:06.591 --> 02:11:08.422
So you know about that, huh?

02:11:08.860 --> 02:11:10.794
I know about everything.

02:11:11.395 --> 02:11:13.386
I'm just trying to figure out
how you did it.

02:11:13.464 --> 02:11:15.091
You think
I'm stealing from you, Ray?

02:11:15.166 --> 02:11:18.431
If the Shaw Agency is gonna
give you a cut of
the 10 percent I'm given them.

02:11:18.502 --> 02:11:21.471
I might as well keep
the goddamn money
in my pocket.

02:11:21.739 --> 02:11:24.037
Leave us alone.
We need to talk.

02:11:25.142 --> 02:11:26.200
Ray.

